text:
I really enjoyed the sushi/burrito fusion they offer here. This was my first trip, and the menu is well laid out. I think you could spend an eternity trying to build your own combination of ingredients, so the pre-designed models are a blessing.  I tried the Redondo (seaweed wrapped, sans cilantro, add ginger), and it was very flavorful.

The staff was attentive and helpful with recommendations. Portions were the right size (not too much, not too little). 

My only recommendation is a little more variety on the pre-designed rolls/burritos for quick ordering. I liked the layout of the menu that highlighted the protein in each design first, so keep it up!

Coolest. Concept. Ever. I know there are others but this was my first and I fell head over heels for this creative take on my favorite cuisine! It's like Chipotle meets Quick sushi...will definitely be a staple in our household! Fish was like buttah...

Finally stopped by and tried a sushi burrito. I pretty much did a 'make your own,' eliminating un-sushi type ingredients from one of their regular items...big mistake I think. Had tuna, yellowtail, masago, cucs and wasabi sauce. The wasabi sauce wasn't spicy enough and just the cucs didn't give enough texture to my burrito. It was still good, just not as good as it might have been if I'd gone with theirs on the menu.
Friendly staff and will stop by the next time I'm in the area for one of Their burritos

Is it a burrito?yes.
How does it taste?AAmazing!
How do you eat it?Anyway you can, trust me you'll find the way "
How is it wraped? Sea wead, or sesame seed wraps.
Is it sushi? Yes!"thats what makes it so good , best of both worlds in one paper wrapping. Soft rice on the outside the crunch in the inside.
Is it mexican food? I would say it's about a 50/50. Salsa bar has both salsa and wasabi."!!! Woa!!
What do you put in it? I say you put in about $20 for two people, we got two different burrito/Roll, they cut in half , we switched halfs to try a little of both.Hip music very fresh feel , check it out !

This place is fabulous. Food is so fresh, refreshing and tasty!  Such a cool concept. Staff was amazing with first timers and owner/gm came out to chat. We arrested the Newport Bach style and another great dish. Along with soup. Would be back again. For sure.
Have been twice in as many days. The food is wonderful and the staff is super friendly and helpful! It is totally worth the 20 minutes drive.
Yum!! Definitely need to make your way there. "Long Beach"! Can be a little crowded so make sure you give yourself enough time if your on a limited lunch hour.

Seriously think it's overpriced. Portions are small considering the price. They give you one small scoop of sushi/fish. Idk maybe bc I'm used to eating "all you can eat" sushi, but I was not full from my burrito/wrap. I prefer to eat at a regular AYCE sushi restaurant to pay $10 more to get 10x more food/portions...then I'll be satiated. While the food does taste good, it's not great sushi/fish for the price your paying. I probably wouldn't come again just bc of the pricing & portions.
Ordered the Rockport burrito sushi 3 times because it was dann amazing. It had crunch and good spice I wish have access to that back in California

I'm very ecstatic to see Jaburrito open back up and so much closer to where I live now! 
However, this place is about 2 weeks old and the employees are still new at this. This is the reason why I'm reviewing this as a 3 stars for now. 
The new staff are not doing a great job at making this, but I will let this slide. 

Except for some few glaring holes: 
One of the guy piled up all of the brown rice in the middle of my seaweed wrap instead of evenly covering up the whole square area, like you see with the white rice. Doing this will cause my burrito to fall apart easily.  They don't put much in your wrap, one lady was counting the pico de gallos on my burrito, I'm not even kidding. I told her to put more on there and she still counting the tiny scoops instead of normal scoops! She been doing 3 tiny scoops of everything instead of 4 like what the last location normally do. Also they put waaaay too much condiments on it, cause it to get really soggy and drowning out the flavours. 

I will be back once everyone settle in and when Taro chips will be available.

First of all I love these burritos. I go to the one on Sahara all the time. When I heard that there was one closer to me I got excited. The food is excellent as always. However, the staff was sub par. There were many people behind the counter grouped in circles just talking to each other. Another customer walks in saying that she had an order she needed to pick up and the employee didn't have an answer to her. I'm ready to pay and the cashier turns around and sneezes into his shoulder facing towards the food! If you have to sneeze never sneeze towards the food. The staff seemed like they never worked in the food industry. I was disgusted with the cashier sneezing. Killed my mood. Excellent food tho!
I can't stay away from this place... It's so Good.. I tried something different today. A Long Beach on a wheat tortilla... I'm in heaven.

Burritos + sushi = amazing!!! 
This place is great, everybody is nice/friendly, and the food... Soo delicious! Definitely going back, the prices here are fare and not wacky like most niche joints.

I got a make your own bowl. I chose the Asada tofu and made it similar to The Broadway but with Avocado Cilantro sauce. The tofu was cooked as soon as I ordered. You can choose between white and brown rice. The portion was very big, so I wasn't expecting to finish it, but I did. The jalapenos weren't very spicy. Veggies tasted fresh. Guac could be better. I got it to go. The container is not good at keeping the food warm but nothing the microwave can't solve. I want to go back and try the jachos. My friend got The Long Beach with green tea and seaweed salad and she loved it.
Great food, lots of choices, and the friendliness and helpfulness of the staff will keep us coming back!
Absolutely fabulous food!!! I just wish you'd open a place in Henderson. I'd definitely make many more stops.

All I can say is BOMB!!! Best alternative to a traditional AYCE Sushi spot. You must go and try the Huntington with extra furikaki seasoning. Oh and the taro chips and dip. Man the best stuff I'm telling you. The west side of Vegas has a lot of sushi poke places but this one takes the cake!!!
The food here is great! The pile on the toppings they are all fresh and very filling. The staff I courteous and attentive I will definitely be returning
This place is ok. They're kinda stingy with the amount of protein. Had to pay for more protein coz they put so little.  Should've gone to Soho sushi burrito.
Sushi burritos here are awesome! Great ingredients, quick service and delicious final product!

Loved the idea they were going with, food was good! But id rather spend my money on chipotle, or on sushi. Not being combined together, to many hot & sweet flavors combined! But the idea of it was very creative!

I went to college at UNLV and honestly we all know how hard it is to grab a great quick healthy bite to eat in Las Vegas.  I went to the opening of this place last week b/c I wanted something besides fast food before my drive home to CA.  Hopefully they open a spot in Newport Beach soon.  This is a great concept!!!

These guys are great. The food is absolutely amazing,  but beyond that the service is just over the top fantastic. Every time I go there the place is clean and the employees are friendly and helpful. I had this ridiculous mishap with Uber eats delivery service today, and even though it wasn't Jaburritos' fault at all, they went out of their way to contact me directly and apologize for not getting my delivery and to see if there was anything they could do to make it right.

Most companies wash their hands of responsibility when there's another independent party involved like that, and that has always frustrated me as a consumer. You usually hear things like, "well it's out of our hands" or "there's nothing we can do" which isn't true and definitely not a good way to show your customers you care about their business. I received two different phone calls from Jaburritos to follow up on my order, and they even got Uber eats to send a second driver out to my place for a completely free order, which is super impressive cause I complained like a crazy person and they were only willing to give me a $5.00 coupon for next time. It's just really refreshing to be treated with so much consideration by the staff. It's sadly rare in the service industry these days. 

Also the food is super good and I like sticking it in my fat face :D

Cool concept, not for a sushi purist, a bit sacrilege.  My biggest complaint is they modified soy sauce to make it thicker and saltier.  Not sure why they don't have actual soy sauce.  The fish itself is good and the prices are fair for what they give you.

Went for a quick lunch bite with the hubster and spawn. My first impression was "Wow! That's a lot of people on the line!" I work at a local line-style restaraunt and we usually have 2-3 on the line as compared to 5-6. The line delegated each task to each person, ensuring quality and precision. 

The line people recommended three burritos based on my tastes. I went with the Baja (yellowtail, spicy tuna, guac, tortilla strips, and some other ingredients I don't recall)  the roll was out quickly and it was so good. The fish was pretty much on par with sushi restaraunts  (none of that grocery store BS)!

The cashier offered taro chips (which were bomb) and a drink. The price was reasonable for how much it filled me up (and their cups are made from plants. How rad is that?) Totally going back!

Being that I'm being lazy on my day off, and that it's been raining all day, I ordered delivery for mine and my dude's meals..

First off, a vegan/vegetarian menu at a sushi place.. whaaaaattt?!!! Even if it tasted awful, kudos for at least offering something for us non-meat/fish eaters! 

I did the build-your-own vegan gardein steak burrito. Sooo many veggie options..
He got the Acapulco burrito.. Seriously, there are so many options even for the wrap.. Seaweed (what I got), wheat, soy.. we also ordered edemame and chips and queso. Did I mention it has a bit of Mexican infusion?! 

As for the food.. absolutely delicious! For everything!! I asked him if he liked his burrito and with a mouthful of food, scarfing it down I got "mmm hmmm".. safe to say he liked it. I feel bad for the guy who delivered it, seeing as how it's raining, but I tipped, so hopefully this makes up for it a little bit. 

They may want to change/update their delivery service app.. I placed the order at 3:03pm, and the email said it would be delivered around 3:13pm..? Even if there was no one in the place and they immediately started the order, it takes around 9 minutes just to drive to my house from there.. we got it in about 23 minutes which in and of itself, is super fast, not to mention, is raining!! (And virtually no one in Vegas knows how to drive in the rain..) Just mentioning that since you'll have the idiot that complains that his food was delivered late, even tho it was an unrealistic amount of time given. 

PLEASE, do yourself a favor and check this place out!!!
A great alternative for my side of town when I can't make it to soho.   Staff is really nice and helpful.  I do love the mochi combo option.

My favorite sushi burrito spot in Vegas! My first visit here, I had plenty of questions regarding their menu    & the staff was very patient with me, answering all my questions & accommodated to all my requests. My favorite is the Rockport in a bowl with greens, tossed in ponzu sauce. So good!

Fresh!!!!
Quick service. I even use UberEats to order from here if I'm feeling lazy on a sunday afternoon.

Highly recommend this place. GO TRY IT NOWWW!!

Thanks!

One of my clients brought me a couple of items to try out. I must say I was pleasantly surprised. Everything I tried (even) the real spicy items were great. The teriyaki steak was my favorite. Tons of flavor and very easy to eat in their hand rolls.

I've had sushi burritos before in CA and really enjoyed. So. When we saw this, we had to have it! It didn't disappoint. The staff was very welcoming and helpful. The selection was extensive and very fresh. The same goes with the sauces they offered. We chose four different items and I tried every single one! We definitely fans!

Incredible! Looking for a quick bite without feeling guilty about what you just put in your body? Then you need to get your self down there. I have no problems saying publicly that I'm addicted to this place! I love the "Redondo". Friendly staff and environment!

Easily my favorite lunch spot! Always super fresh, the staff is awesome and we were so excited to find out they're planning on expanding to other areas of the valley!

I usually get the Long Beach! It's definitely enough for a meal by itself. :)
I created my own bowl two proteins was too much but it was delicious. I also got the mango sake which I didn't know was 20 (way to expensive) but it was just okay.

LOVE this place. 
I had it for the first time and I cannot get enough of it. 
My personal favorite is the Long Beach very tasty.
Only wish is that they can expand Jaburritos more,  I'm from Cali and I was only in Vegas for the weekend.

I visit Jaburritos once, sometimes twice a week and every time, the food is delicious, the people are nice and they keep the place clean. My favorite go-to is the Redondo wrapped in seaweed.

You have the choice of picking from their Chef's Creations (like the Redondo) or you can create your own. Get it wrapped like a burrito or in a bowl. Either way you choose, the portions are pretty decent size. Definitely get your money's worth.

Our first time to Jaburrito; and I really liked the "Redondo" burrito with soy paper and sushi rice. My hubby ordered the "Huntington" w/ similar setup. The burritos were fresh and yummy; albeit I used a lot of soy sauce to add additional flavor. The line staff were really friendly. I look forward to my next visit. :)

BY FAR, THE BEST SUSHI BURRITO I've had in Vegas! This was not my first sushi burrito experience, but I would be happy if it was my last! The service was friendly, fast and helpful. More importantly, the food was fresh and tasty! 

The simple answer for 5 stars: consistent quality of ingredients, menu options and service. Unlike some of the competition, you won't get an oversized hand roll of below average sushi. The sauce options are plentiful and flavorful. Also, being able to have surf and turf (chicken and steak) options is a huge plus in my book! I usually order a sushi burrito - yellowtail + spicy tuna is my go to - with a steak and surimi (crab) Jacho (nacho) to share. The price and serving sizes are great too (try the bowls!).

This is a very weird phenomenon that I am new to, but I will say that I enjoyed it. It's essentially sushi, just not cut.

This specific place is one where every employee was memorably helpful and nice, each had a genuine smile on their face (see photos). The first guy that took our order explained how it worked and made some helpful suggestions. I was going to skip on the HOMEMADE taro chips and then when I saw them on my friend's plate, I had to have them. They looked delicious and they tasted amazing. 

I will say, it's a bit of a weird smell when you first walk in - not from the building or anything - just a whole mix of food smells in general. Also, the eating area isn't exactly homey - like it's not personally my ideal date place, but it's very clean and fine with friends. It's a married date place - ha!!

Yes, this place is great, go try it.

Good sushi burritos but they charging way too much for these! For 2 extra meats in my roll I paid almost as much as 2 separate ones! You're better off going to To See Roll down the street for poke bowls, way cheaper and they give you a lot more. I expected more from this place. Even the inside was alright, just your average fast food style restaurant. I honestly wouldn't go back unless someone offers to buy me food here, then I'll be at Jaburritos! Shoot I almost never say no to free food!

What can I say...? Everything I have had here has been super yummy! From the burritos to the even the kids meals, you can't go wrong.  My 4 year old daughter loves this place, she usually gets the california burrito roll or the shrimp tempura bowl.  The taste is so fresh and their sauces are so savory.   And they have sushi cupcakes!!! So cute and so tasty!

First time coming to this jaburrito. we really enjoy sushi burritos but probably not gonna come back to this one. bad customer service from one of the workers making my burrito. normally you have the choice of adding more topping or sauces. he didn't even ask me and when he started rolling up my burritos i asked if i could add more toppings, he looks at me with a disgusted look and says "what you want?" with attitude. 

customer service is part of your job, if you can't provide that being the face of the company, might wanna find another job.

I would rather make that far drive and go to soho burrito, I was so excited that I found this place because it was closer to home.... But the staff the lack of customer service made this place such a turn off compared to soho. There was about 8 employees in the order area, then they kept passing my order to another staff member... All while instead of paying attention to my food and me as the customer they were chit chatting like bunch of hormonal teenagers. I got to the point where I was over it before I was got my order, and asked if they were affiliated with Soho one guy was so quick to give me a look of death and said no... He then looked at the female staff and literally gave her a look as if I didn't see him... When I paid and walked away they said hell no we're not soho you crazy... Just like immature teenagers... I will never come back and eventually other people who see how your staff acts
Delish and fun! It's super quick and healthy- all of my favorite things in life. The long beach is amazing!

Came here for the first time personally after work to grab some dinner. Not bad of a line slightly before dinner time, around 5-6 o clock on a Sunday afternoon. Friendly staff. 

Previously i had ordered a burrito that my friend picked up for me which was a decent size. This time, by recommendation for "more filling meal", i had ordered a bowl instead. 

I had realized the only one i've been ordering all this time is Redondo. The Redondo consists of ahi tuna, salmon, yellowtail, red onion, jalapeno, topped with masago, tortilla strips, cilantro, and wasabi mayo. 

They take each order separately and will ask you how many orders you are doing. When i saw how much rice they put into the bowl, i was happy. XD I thought i'd have to ask for more (like i usually do for Chipotle) but it is quite the amount. They use a really small scoop, like a melon baller scoop for the fish but its still a decent amount to saturate the bowl pretty decently while eating. Red onions give a nice sweet and crispness while jalapeno and wasabi mayo gives it a nice punch ! According to some friends, there seem to be more tortilla strips than normal but i didnt mind. Was a nice snack while eating the bowl. Lol 

Speed in ordering wasn't too bad. Fairly decent for what it is. Could be a faster but can't complain. I've been to the other location Soho Sushiburrito on Sahara and it was much smaller than this location and much slower service. Different names on menu but identical ingredients. This is a much more spacious and easier to access location. 

They have a side bar of various salsas, wasabi, and a place for you to get soy sauce as well.

Decent location right off Rainbow and 215, northbound on rainbow, next to Rosallie's. 

Bowl is an amazing deal and will definitely fill you up pretty well. Burrito for the not so big eaters as its still a decent size. Highly recommended place for a quick bite of some fresh seafood.
Hands down the best sushi burritos in town. Chips and cheese are amazing. Highly recommended.

I am giving 5 stars for now ... based on how amazing the food was ... a little disorganized the process of making the food, but it was only open 3 days ... I am sure it will get better. Hopefully the line don't get worse:)

It was sooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooo yummy!
Ja Burritos is AMAZING! I eat here at least once a week. The staff, food and environment is all great.

Run, don't walk to Jaburrito! This place is for reals amazing! I went twice within three days and was able to try 4 of the burritos; the Mission, Rosarito, Long Beach and Redondo. They are all so different and delicious! I think the Long Beach was by far my favorite. The fish is fresh and prepared perfectly. The sauces are full of flavor and paired perfectly with each burritos ingredients. The service is perfection. And the prices can't be beat! I can't wait to get back to Vegas to eat there again.
It is just like I remembered, delicious! I've been there 3 times since it opened on Rainbow. I always get the create your own (I have fun that way). The staff was friendly. I'll be coming here a lot.

I have always wanted to try sushi burritos and I am glad that I had my first taste here. 

The service is very fast and courteous. The prices were quite reasonable and the location was very clean. 

I got the Redondo Sushi burrito, which had Ahi Tuna, Salmon, Yellowtail, Cucumber, Masago, Red Onion, Tortilla Strips, Jalapeño, Cilanto, and Wasabi Mayo. All of the above for only about $13. That's a steal. Furthermore, it tasted absolutely fantastic, definitely hit the craving for some sushi. 

Overall, I would highly recommend this to anyone who wants to try something new and be able to *ahem* instagram something fun.

Love the place. Good quality food. It's no big deal but I order food from here with Uber eat, not sure if it's the delivery or this location but I didn't get my drinks . Thirsty customer enjoying your burrito but no drinks to wash it down.
Yummy yummy yummy! Some sushi burritos have that tough seaweed wrap on them, here it's crispy and bites off easily! Products are always so fresh and not so fishy! I thoroughly enjoy this restaurant!

This review is for anyone already familiar with the other location which was Jaburrito and is now Soho sushi burrito.   

       Went today for the first time and, although the freshness was spot on, they are lacking in a few areas.  
1. No taro chips.   Get them.  People love them
2. No finishing roller machine thingy.  Yes.  That's my name for it because what else is that thing called?   Our burritos fell apart very easily because this was different.
3. WAY smaller burritos.   I think this has to do with their limited "rolling" abilities as well.  
4. Slow staff.   This is to be expected with a new place.    I agree with another reviewer in that it seems like they count how many pico tomato cubes they put on.  Lol

     So basically, very tasty but needs work compared to Soho sushi burrito.

******Went back on 5/25/16******

1. Taro chips!    thicker and more oily than Soho's.   Furikake dusting not as tasty.
2. This hand roller still lacks.  Only a few employees seem to know how to roll them tighter. 
3. Better job with size. 
4. Staff speed has increased.   No longer counting every ingredient they put on.  

      With some work, they should get better.

This place is pretty much the same as a few of the other sushi burrito places in the area except that it has a little more of a mexican fusion type feel. They even offer tortilla and guacamole and other things that other sushi burrito places don't usually offer. I didn't get any of that though, I stuck with a more sushi type of burrito. 

I liked that they cut the fish smaller than most places. I didn't like the way they cut the cucumbers. I personally like my cucumbers without skin for sushi burritos.

Their price point is less than a lot of other sushi burrito places, but you also get smaller portion sizes. I ordered the same toppings that I get at other places, but my burrito was smaller and didn't fill me up as much. 

The staff was okay, but they weren't very friendly or welcoming. The interior of the place was also kind of weird. It had an an institutional type of feeling. I'm not an expert on interior design or anything like that, but it just didn't feel comfortable in there. 

So overall the food was pretty good, but nothing special unless you really want Mexican style sushi burritos. I'm going to stick with sweet poke down the road

Finally got to try some sushi burritos & glad that we went here!
The service was friendly & helpful. I got the Long Beach burrito wrapped in soy paper & despite it having guacamole (which I usually can't stand) - it tasted amazing! My mom had the Kodiak sushi burrito wrapped in soy paper. She loved her's as well. We both enjoyed our food a lot & would love to go again. We wish there was a location closer to where we live but we know that the trip is worth it for the food either way!
So glad this opened up by my house now, I used to drive to the old location often just for a Kodiak..mmmm...wish I had one now, but they're closed at this hour. Highly recommend!
Great food with healthy selections when you are on the go.  I stopped by for a quick lunch and will definitely bring going here again

My first time trying the "sushi burrito" craze. Was close to my work so decided to try it with a co-worker today. Busy at around 12:15-12:30pm. Waited in line for about 10 minutes to place our orders. Ordered the Baja & my co-worker ordered the Rockport as well as their tarro chips & sauce. I didn't try her burrito but did try the tarro chips & sauce. It was good. My Baja burrito was good but it's not something I am craving to go back for. I feel the burrito needed a bit of salt to make the flavors really pop. There were a few other burritos on the menu that sounded good so I'll have to give them a try some time.
Exceeded our expectations by sooooo much. This place will become a regular dining option. The cupcakes were cute and good. It's fun to figure out how to eat them!

Great service and great food! 

I was really excited to try this place, but I feel like I got kind of tired of it halfway through my burrito, it was just so much food (which is NOT a bad thing!). I mean it was no fault of Jaburritos, but I  think I will stick to my normal sushi! 

I do like the area that this Jaburrito is in! It's really fun and a really cute area to kind of hide away from the main craziness of the strip for a little bit.

Jaburrito is one of the BEST sushi burritos in town! They offer a huge variety of rolls and bowls. I always go with the soy paper and it's always good! I custom my order with surimi crab and shrimp tempura and add some cream cheese to it. They have a large variety of sides available to put in your burrito, more than other places have. Check them out they have two locations! One of rainbow and also one located in the Linq! You're welcome in advance!

I finally got a chance to try this place out after hearing good things. I was really impressed with the freshness of the ingredients. Being that it was my first time, the staff was very helpful and friendly. I got my order pretty quickly, and chose to have it wrapped in seaweed, rather than like your traditional burrito. I will definitely come back again in the near future. I decided to give four stars simply cause I felt the price point could be a little better.
Yummm yummm yummmm! Had a Long Beach and it was soooo onto! And got me a make your own jaburrito the one star is for not having a fruit punch at the fountain drnk

Looking very inconspicuous from the outside, don't let that put you off. Inside you will find a unique and delicious dining experience. The fusion of Sushi and burritos works to a "T" here. There is a plethora of combinations that you can eat in a burrito, in a bowl, or on a type of nachos. I tried the Redondo beach as a burrito. The sushi was fresh and tasty. They also offer very reasonably priced add on's like edamame and seaweed salad.   If you're looking for a delicious and inexpensive meal you don't have to dress up for, check this place out.

Since this is the only restaurant with this concept in Vegas it does make it unique for now until Vegas starts catching on with the poke bowl hype in CA. I have now been to this location, and I went to their last location Soho. I'm not sure what people are saying about a different menu. It looks identical! The pictures are the same and all. I liked being able to customize my burrito but everything tastes pretty bland and the portion size is tiny! My husband customized his burrito and it ended up being $28 for 2 burritos and 1 soda. I think that's steep for the size of it. My husband customized his order and I think $1.50 for each protein is a lot when you ask for tamago and you get two 1/2 inch piece. The woman ringing us up had to talk to several people in order to figure out how to ring us up. She couldn't figure it out and needed various opinions. The owner was not in the assembly line of people but he did come out after and ended up coming over and was nice enough to fix it all and apologized. 

My burrito was made with rice paper and brown rice. At the last location it all stayed together. This burrito was soggy and it soaked through the rice paper and it ripped apart making it impossible to pick up. Switching to seaweed was helpful with holding the burrito together. 

I did not see the salsa bar like the last location  which was a turn off with the store bought Pace Picante type salsa and I'm sorry raw fish and salsa just don't go well together. I get it is "burrito" and "sushi" but for me I think sushi burritos would be better with ponzu or something that pairs well with raw fish. 

I still don't get the nacho cheese with taro chips. Also why does their nachos have tortilla chips? Would be so much better with wonton chips. 

As far as the people working there, you have a poor woman who is really trying but she is so slow and forgets things. She also uses gloves then touches doors and other things (pet peeve of mine- why are you touching my food with your bare hands then touching walls and doors?grrr) you also have someone having a hard time ringing people up. Also when I ask for light on the sauce, I really would like light on the sauce. Just like Subway I ask for light mustard and I get 3 tablespoons. The same thing happened here. Light means soaked in sauce.  Maybe I will be back if they fix some of the issues I mentioned.

Came for my first time and I absolutely loved it! So much variety, you are not limited to only burritos. You can upgrade to a salad bowl and pick your favorite choices. This will definitely be a regular spot of mine :) I recommend the avocado cilantro sauce!

It's good for lunch. Interesting concept that turns out to be yummy and satisfying. Sushi burritos, salads and bowls! - I would like to see other chips though. Taro or plantain for example. They need to add more seating. And too many people working  and not as fast. It is perfect for a power lunch!

Jaburritos, with the recent influx of sushi burrito and poké bowl shops that have opened everywhere in Vegas, Jabburitos is still "King" of the sushi burrito imho. Get the "Redondo" sushi burrito. You will not be disappointed. The staff was very friendly and I think one of the owners walks around and greets all the tables and asks everyone's opinions. Very personable touch.

Very good but their guacamole is not the best. I like the Long Beach and just change guacamole for avocado and it taste yummy. Love it here!!! This is my new favorite spot even my little ones like it.
I had a make your own burrito. Got food poisoning from it and threw up 5 times. My guess is from the salmon. Their food safety is lacking, it's probably not kept at the proper temperature.

The same friendly service and solid sushi-burrito menu is now available on the Southwest side of town, closer to their original Soho restaurant. Fish quality is decent, the hand-held rolls get the majority of their flavor from added sauces and salsas, as is the case at most Americanized sushi joints.

The BAJA ($9) is my preference, with a fresh salsa that really makes it shine as a fusion dish rather than just a large sushi roll. The MALIBU ($8) was a little basic, and the LONG BEACH was a step up- as expected, since it contains more fish and a higher price tag to match ($11).

Note the salsa bar around the corner by the register- actual salsas are available, as well as more traditional sushi accouterments like soy sauce, wasabi, and ginger. While the original location is more convenient to me, I'm sure I'll pop in when I visit the coffee shop next door.

Skimpy on portions of meat and on sides.  Rang up a 2 item build your own with the more expensive as the primary and the cheaper as the add on thereby charging $2 more than their competition for the same roll.

My first time coming here and the staff was very friendly and explained the menu and options to me. I chose the Rockport and you can choose to have it in a flour burrito, seaweed burrito, bowl, or nachos. I had mine in a seaweed burrito. It was really good. Good portion size as well. I also had the taro chips and cheese. The cheese is standard issue but the chips were very good. They have a unique, almost sweet taste to them. Highly recommend them as well. The restaurant itself was clean and well maintained. We came in the late afternoon (3pm) so there was no line or no wait to order. I will be back again and again.

This was my first sushi burrito experience and thank goodness I had it here. I was not let down in the slightest. The ingredients were fresh, service was friendly, helpful and quick. 

What I love about Jaburritos is the menu. This is very much a Chipotle setup. You can choose a burrito, bowl, or nachos. You have a chef's creation menu on one side and then a build your own on the other. You can customize all the way up to what you want your burrito wrapped in. Classic seaweed? Soy paper? Tortilla? They have plenty of sauce choices like wasabi mayo, Yuzu Avocado Cilantro, Mango Teriyaki. It's your choice how adventurous you want to be. 

Seeing as it was my first time, and how unfamiliar I am with the sushi burrito concept, I didn't decide to build my own for fear of greatly ruining my own experience with bad decisions. I ordered a chef's creation, The Redondo. I added avocado, cause why the hell not? And just like chipotle, it costs extra. That never gets old. 

They have a bar of self serve wasabi, ginger, soy sauce, cilantro, etc. This took it over the top for me. I love A LOT of ginger. So it was nice to be able to help myself. 

I will definitely be returning to try different menu items. Possibly a sushi bowl is next on the list? Thank god this place is close to work. New lunch spot? I think yes.
Service was great and my sushi burrito was delicious! The employees were really kind as well. So happy there is a sushi burrito place near my house now
Good, convenient, prices are competitive to other places. Food has always been fresh and place is clean. Friendly service.

Good product good service. My 4 year old daughter wouldn't touch anything on this menu but after I ordered my Redondo Burrito and Taro Chips with Queso, one of the employees came by and chatted with her and gave her a free mochi ice cream. Took care of us! 

Burrito was great, lots of flavors. Taro Chips and queso was ok, need to increase the size of the queso ramekin. The chip to queso ratio was probably 10/1 Haha. All in all, I'll go back!

Great concept, it's like the Sushirrito chains in San Francisco. Had no idea that this place even existed had I not needed to take my son to anthem pediatrics, so it was a pleasant surprise to know this place is open. Was really excited to try it out, and got a Rockport and a Huntington. I know they just opened, hence the 3 stars, but service could be a lot better. They were a little confused and disorganized, and I had to repeat my order a couple of times since they screwed up and gave me two rockports instead. We ate the food when we got home, so it didn't taste as good as I expected it to, but I'm sure it would have been better if we ate the food as soon as we got them. Totally taking the blame on that one! We will probably try this place out again as I really like the concept, and would probably take the time to actually eat the food there while it's fresh . Crossing my fingers that the staff work better as a team next time!

I really wanted this place to be better then Soho SushiBurritos.... Since the location of JaBurritos is so much better for me. It is less then 10 minutes from my house.... So freaking cool!!! 

But sadly the flavors and the staff were not up to par.  

Overall my experience was average.  The staff were not very friendly but they weren't rude either... They were just eh....(2.5/5). I got my food to go but decided to eat in.... The entire time I was dining in not one person came to ask me how it was... How I liked the food. Not one word. :/ Even as i walked in...I didn't get a greeting like they did to everyone else that entered while i ate....I barely got a hi when I was planning my order. Overall... Not like SushiBurritos at all. :(. 

The food was ok as well. The rice was not as flavorful as well. *Sigh* i got a create your own with sarimi crab.... Which is just the crab filling from the California roll. :) It was decent but it not seasoned enough... Just a hint more of soy sauce or salt I think would have made it alot better. They did have a bunch of ingredients which were awesome... And they even had fresh jalapenos which is a huge plus in my book. :) So overall it was ok...(3/5)

Ambiance was pretty cool. It was clean and very bright. They had a decent sauce area like you would find in any Mexican place. (4.5/5)

Overall, most likely I will be back as this place is so close to me... But if time permits I'd rather goto SushiBurritos.

Pretty good sushi burritos. Standard experience if you've ever been to one of these places before. Basically you get a giant Americanized sushi roll and eat it like a burrito. Fish was fresh, as were the rest of the ingredients. I liked it, if ever in the mood for sushi burrito this would be my current pick.

Great service, very quick and quality food. 

I got the Laguna- I'm a sucker for unagi and it was so flavorful and soft. 

I would just suggest sauce cups to mix wasabi and soy sauce for dipping. 

I could eat here everyday! Yum!
Ordered group take out from this place.  Super nice.  Came 15 min earlier then the scheduled time and the food was already ready for pick up. Yummy!!

Got the Rockport and Long Beach...both were delicious. Line was long but moved fast because they had lots of people working, they originally had 2 lines: 1 to order and 1 to pay, but they realized people were waiting in line for too long so they asked us to take a seat and called us up to pay when the food so ready which was nice. The only down size is the price, pretty pricy for the portion. I do realize that it's fresh fish and fish is pricy but for a "fast-food" style it is pricy. Got two combos, 1 with seaweed salad and the other with the taro chips ($.50 extra) that came with queso, the queso tasted thick and weird, chips were too oily, the oil leaked through the bag! Seaweed salad was really good!! Definitely should try!!

Amazing sushi burrito joint went here out of spite with my girlfriend after grabbing some boba. Had the rockport sushi burrito. Though service wasn't so friendly look as if some of the workers hated their lives. A bit on the pricy side compared to other sushi burrito places i've been too. On the other hand what won me over is the food. Would love to come back some time.
Found this spot while looking for some healthy and delicious options while enjoying a girls' trip. Wish we had this up in the Bay Area!

My fourth time here, but my first review. This one is purely for outstanding customer service, in addition to the delicious food. Not only was every member of the team here a friendly, engaging personality, but they truly went above and beyond! So, if none of you have ever gone with me for food, let me start by saying that I am one of the most waffling people when it comes to a good menu full of delicious food! Business owners: if I can't decide what I want from your menu, that's a good sign that I love what I'm seeing and your menu is probably great. Anyways, back to Jaburrito's. The gal at the counter was so helpful and friendly, that not only did she propose a solution to one part of my indecisiveness (getting 2 smaller, but equally scrumptious hand rolls of different flavors rather than one large sushi burrito), but she also then surprised my friend and I by bringing a small sample bowl of their newest flavor to our table! Almost no one shows that level of commitment to the happiness of their customers, especially not the needier ones who can sometimes (I'm sure) be obnoxious with their indecisiveness. I would give a 6th star if I could, will tell anyone who will listen about this outstanding experience, and can't wait to be back for another great lunch at Jaburrito's.
Yummo!  First time having a sushi burrito and it was excellent!

Beyond delicious. The Redondo & Rockport are the favorites. Staff is amazing. They are happy to make any changes to any preset burritos without hesitation. Love the option to combo meals. Taro chips/cheese & different mochi flavors are great!  Everything is fresh and yummy. Have even purchased burritos for lunch the following day and everything held up beautifully. Make sure to sign up for their more than generous loyalty club.

Had a Rolls of Redondo and Long beach. Redondo didn't have much taste but they gave me Eel sauce. Also brown rice was little too soft. But Long beach was the bomb! Hope they carry Aloha Shoyu for condiment!
Wow wow wow. Once you have the Redondo Japanese burrito you won't think about another roll of sushi in your life. This stuff is healthy!!! I recommend like to other place.

Venice vegan burrito  YES! Gardein beef can totally be a hit or miss but in this case it was totally a hit! Burrito had so much flavor!

Ordered through Uber Eats - restaurant forgot our chips with our order but the restaurant refunded us immediately which was super awesome! 

Thank you for an awesome vegan option at your restaurant! Will be back for sure!

After finding about this new craze. Sushi burritos. I was dieing to try. So we were in the area and my husband went in and got us some. He got the Baja and the Huntington (I think that's what it was called). So we had both of each. 

I for one love burritos and sushi so I thought maybe both of them together would be a homerun. Not so much. I was left disappointed. Not sure why. It's just wasn't as good as I wanted it to be. I probably won't be coming back for more. Or probably won't try this concept again at all.

All I can say aside from the great location, fast, friendly, service, amazing quality of food, happy atmosphere, clean place, everyone smiling, couldn't ask for anything else! Jaburrito has earned a customer for life!

I've been waiting my online order more than 40 minutes,too crezy!They were missing my online order,when I got there ,everyone was chitchat ,no now knew my order, servers sucks,it was my first also my last time

Update: Management contacted me and offered to have me come back so they could correct the mistake. I'm truly not out to get a free meal, so I ordered once more through Postmates and my food was perfect. Great food, great management.
Sushi burritos looked delicious on their advertisements but not in real life. $10-$15 a burrito, limited fish and was flavorless.

I had the rockport it was SO good. I love this concept. I had it with tempura shrimp without the raw tuna and in a soy wrapper. I was stuffed. The edamame was a little undercooked. I hope this place continues to be successful. I loved Soho when it first opened and it continues to be my favorite sushi place. The other location has a different owner but same menu.

I'm not gonna lie but I'm really impressed with their sushi burritos. I haven't tried the bowl yet but one day! I've always gone for the Redondo and the Long Beach. 

Oh wait, are the sushi burritos named after places in Southern California!?

This place gets busy during lunch on the weekends. I would recommend stopping by late afternoon or early evening.

Tried Jaburrito on Sahara (Now called SOHO Sushi Burrito, which is probably under different management) and we fell in love. Service was great, the workers were fast to put everything together and of course the burrito was amazing! I was so excited to see a Jaburrito opening up on rainbow which is closer to my home.

However we had a complete opposite experience when we came to Jaburrito on rainbow. 

Major disappointments
1. Before we began to build our burrito, I had asked the guy if they had Salmon. Immediately we were lied to as the guy told us "No, we,re all out." And because My friend and I looked at each other and thought to ourselves if we should just go b/c we both had the cravings for salmon.. The guy than says, "Oh... Oh wait we can cut it for you in the back if you could just give us about 10 minutes" ......Um we're thinking I thought there was NONE left ?? o.O 
2. After waiting the 10 minutes and they were ready to build our burrito, it was time to choose our rice. I chose brown rice while my friend chose white rice. My friends white rice came ready out of the machine, while the girl handling my burrito had to spread the brown rice on the wrap instead. Which btw took at least five minutes.... I felt bad b/c if was holding up the line and it looked like she was doing this for the first time. All the workers looked a bit confused, kind of just standing around and they were not working as fast as the other location on Sahara.
3. Aside from being lied to, the main reason we will Not be coming back to the rainbow location is because Both my rice and my friends rice taste horrible. My brown rice and my friends White rice were both extremely Mushy, sour and unpleasantly hard to swallow. We came home and were excited to eat our burrito but unfortunately we were so disappointed we opened up the burritos and only ate the insides while leaving the rice. 
4. In addition, they had NO taro chips.

I felt like I wasted my money at this location. We were still hungry and went back out to get food else where.

It's definitely no soho burritos, one of the employees who was asking the customers what they wanted to order was complaining to every customer how hot it was behind the bar. Definitely not as much bang for your buck when it comes to burrito size, and mine was nearly too spicy to eat and I love spicy food. Also the taro chips were stale. Overall Soho Sushi burritos wins by far.
always fresh and easy.   i order sometimes thru ubereats and the food comes in well prepared and still fresh.

Wow! Really hits the spot. 

I can't count how many times I've craved sushi and had to order a ton just to get full.  Here their sushi burrito.  It's just a giant sushi roll. It is absolutely filling, and a great price!  

I don't know why I've bookmarked this and kept putting it off.  It's really good!  If you are on the go and quick and easy. 

I love the options.  I ordered the mission and substituted Ebi for shrimp tempura.  Was almost regretting a flour tortilla.  The tortilla is very thin and doesn't take away from the roll.  I don't love seaweed, since these are much larger than sushi... Might've been overpowering for me.  The yuzu avocado sauce was great, could have had more. 

I am very satisfied and I highly recommend.

If it were up to me I would eat here everyday.  I love this concept and usually get it delivered via UberEATS about 2-3 times per week.  I always start with a spicy tuna roll and start to add toppings.  I love it!
The mochi ice cream is one of the best I tried. I will recommend the matcha mochi flavored ice cream. Highly recommended for the mochi ice cream.
Bomb dot com! It was so good that I went 2 days in a row. There's nothing like this in California, well, there is but it doesn't taste like this place at all!
Best tip is to order online to avoid the lines! Ordered the Redondo and the Ahi Tuna bowls. Great value with the bowls than the burritos.

This place is overly staff.  I've been here twice and both times employees are taking over guests settings.  It looks very unattractive.  

Now as for service, cashiers definitely needs more of a friendly approach. They are like robots most of the time.  

Now for the burritos, it's good, fresh.  We usually order the redondo and have always enjoyed.  I just we could enjoy at the table where all the employees congregate.

Fresh ingredients, friendly customer service, and just such a cool concept! It's like a chipotle where they build the burrito in front of you as you choose your sushi items. Huge portions so go hungry!

This place has been good & sometimes great. That's why I'm giving it a solid 4 stars.
    Quality of the fish has been in a range of 3 to 5 stars, I really wish it was more consistent. I eat a sushi burrito once a week. Unless I do an ayce sushi, but definitely once a week for my sushi/fish fix. This restaurant does have some great sides, I'd recommend you try all of them and all the flavors. Took me a couple months to do so. But I was overall satisfied with everything. It will come down to preference when picking your flavors. 
   The inside of the restaurant is pretty clean. I haven't seen anything that grossed me out or turned me away. The staff friendliness is pretty on point. It's a food spot that is right above average and I hope to see them around for a while. It's the only one I'll go out of my way for when craving a sushi burrito.

Ok so they finally opened another Jaburritos and I guess I finally ate at Jaburritos/Soho Burritos. Being a huge fan of the Soho restaurant and seeing how a lot of people have raved about the original location I was definitely excited. And apparently I wasn't the only one since the line almost made it out the door. Sushi burritos who'd figure!?

If you've never been it's kind of like Chipotle/Subway for sushi rolls. You can customize your roll by first choosing your protein which includes spicy tuna, cajun albacore, salmon, steak, chicken, and more. Then how do you want it, as a salad/rice bowl, wrapped it a tortilla like a burrito, rolled as sushi, or with chips like nachos. Then your sauces and toppings. If you're not great at customizing get one off the menu they all sound good and prices ranged from about $5 to about $11 and of course the customized on could be whatever price.

I went with the Baja which included yellowtail, spicy tuna, cilantro, red onion, cabbage, tortilla strips, guac, lettuce, jalapeños, and a zuzu avocado cilantro sauce. It wasn't that bad. Honestly I was kind of disappointed at the size. I've heard a lot of it being huge. Even saw many pics where rolls dwafted peoples hands. In about 3 of my normal bites it would've been gone. People really do have tiny hands foreal! Drink plenty of water or soda, nibble, or dish out more get another roll.

I was told by an employee that they're not serving everything the original location has.

Inside I counted 14 tables with 2 chairs each so there's enough room for 28 . It's not elbow to elbow seating so they could probably but a few more tables and chairs. 

As of now it's 3.5 stars from me. I like em but not enough to give em the 4th star.

This time I brought a coworker and my son and we dined in. I also tried bowls as opposed to my usual burrito and it just didn't measure up. It all started badly when I ordered and the cute guy with the green eyes that's super friendly wasn't there.
 :( Instead I got the stern, less enthusiastic lady that was clearly impatient. If I didn't order quick enough the lady just kept asking me the same question to put the pressure on. Smh. Service really is a game changer when you're looking for your Poke burrito/bowl go to spot. The food is nearly the same everywhere.

The bowl didn't have as much flavor as my usual burrito. Yes, I got the Redondo again! It seemed like it just needed a double order of sauce or maybe just a drizzle on top. Also the chopped jalapeños all ended up on one side of the bowl, maybe there should be a method to mix it in with the fish because that was a very unpleasant (yet funny) surprise. We had our lunch date here because they actually have something cooked for kids that I saw on the online menu and even though it was bland being just chicken and rice it's nice that they even have an option. Most of these types of places do not. 

I'll be back eventually but I'll be hoping for the nice, patient guy with green eyes or someone who actually wants to earn a big fat tip by being friendly and kind. Since there are 6 of these places in my neighborhood Ill end up going to the place with the nicest employees and since Ja Burritos is the furthest it'll take a little more than good food to get me back on the regular.

Food: 3.5/5 (Malibu, Kodiak).  The 2 burritos I ordered weren't bad.  They're good options if you don't wanna spend $20+ at a regular sushi joint.  I just wasn't too keen on having lettuce added to my sushi.

Service:  5/5.  It probably took less than 5 minutes for 'em to make 3 burritos I ordered.  And, the employees were all nice.

Ambience:  3/5.  The interior is basically a clean fast food joint.

I'll be coming back.  I'll just tell 'em to hold the lettuce...
I really enjoyed the food here but it just made me want to go to an all you can eat sushi place as I am a really big eater.
Freakin awesome....can't ask for more! I'm glad they're closer to me now! Long Beach n Huntington one of my favorite on the menu a must try!

I heard about this place and I had to try it out.
Well after the first time I went back and then again and again.
Burrito is packed with fish not lettuce or other fillers and very tasty. ( you get your money's worth)
I have tried 5 different burritos and have not been disappointed yet.
Friendly staff, conveniently located off the 215 and Russell.
Easy menu
Prices are reasonable
Very Very clean. 
I love the fact that I can eat sushi on the go when I do not have time to eat in.

Just had a burrito delivered via UberEats, gotta try it. I had multiple question and special accommodations and the staff was very friendly and helpful. The food was awesome and matched my service. BRAVO Jaburritos, keep it up!

This place surprised me. I had the Redondo which had tuna, salmon, yellowtail....  They did not scrimp on the ingredients... it tasted really good. The price was reasonable and the crew was friendly and helpful... I will be back !!!

Great sushi, great customer service. Everyone greets you when you walk in the door. It was my first time there and they took the time to explain the whole menu. While eating the employees walked around and made sure everyone's food was to expectation and asked the customers for any recommendations on how they can improve. 

They also gave a short lesson on the history of the restaurant and how it was created. Good service for a small quick bite to eat.

I really love coming here for a quick, clean burrito. I come here often. I would've given 5 stars, but the qualify of burrito differs at times. Always good but sometimes it's sloppy or skimpy and other times it's busting at the seams. All in all one of my go to, during the week dinner pickup places

Finally, a sushiburrito in the southwest part of town. I am a big fan of the one on Sahara. This is so much closer to home. I got the Rodondo and it is the same as the 3 amigos at the Sahara location. Fish were very fresh and for this week they are having 15% off your meal since it is their soft opening. Will be back for more...
Loved it. I can't believe it took me so long to try a sushi burrito. Absolutely love that I can make my order with brown rice . I never see Brown rice sushi unless it's at the grocery store.

Was there on a saturday evening. There were a few people in line but it goes fast. My husband and I ordered the redondo and the rockport burrito. It was just okay. I ate few times at the Soho burrito on Sahara and the burritos at Jaburrito is extremely small compared to Soho. It's almost half the size even though they are the most expensive burritos on the menu with supposedly more ingredients then the other ones on the menu. I can't imagine how much smaller the others are. With all the other sushi burrito joints popping around I will not be returning to this location.

Jaburrito for lunch today! They are alive and well on the corner of rainbow and Patrick. Totally a separate entity from soho sushi burrito. Even though the menu is the same, just with different names lol. The staff is super friendly. Went with my favorite the long beach and it was soooo good!!! Nothing else would do today. They need to open a location in green valley/Henderson next.

The staff is friendly and the food is good. They are a little slow and the operation isn't very smooth, but I'm sure with time all that will improve. It's a new place so I'm sure they are working out kinks and getting into the swing of things. I'll be back, it's nice to have a sushi burrito spot on the southwest side of town.

First time here, after living in Vegas and always passing by, and I would love to say this shit was delicious. Very helpful staff and recommended the rockport. Great recommendation bc like I said "shit was delicious!" I will def be back again!!!!!

It's just okay. It satisfied my hunger, but isn't something that I would crave or rave about; I think because they go pretty heavy on the sauce. I ordered the Laguna something (the one with eel) and a kids Cali, and both were super wet and salty from the sauces.

Wow this was a random walk in on the strip with a WTF trial.  I AM SOOO GLAD I WALKED IN.  It was awesome fresh fast and I will visit again the next time I am in Vegas.  I wish they had one in l Dallas!

Pretty freaking good. I make my own, and I do it super simple. Shredded crab, fresh salmon, screaming O sauce, chipotle mayo, cucumber and fish eggs. Super yummy and satisfies a sushi craving without busting the bank. Been here twice so far and will continue coming!

In my opinion, there's not much that separates this place from the other sushi burrito places that been popping up all over town.

Pros:
--All of the workers greeted me when I walked in, and I mean ALL OF THEM yelled "Welcome to Jaburritos" at the same time!
--Place was clean with lots of tables to eat at.
--Their ingredients were fully stocked.
--Nice location, easy to find.

Cons:
--I was the only person ordering and the whole process went soooooooo slow! Even the person at the register talked so slow to the point where I felt myself crunch my eyebrows.
--One person took all my order and passed the list to another person who made it. I felt like that was more time consuming in my situation although I'm sure thats a very good idea when it's packed in there. 

Just a side note:
--It really bothered me how the guy put my bowl in the bag sideways and then turned it upwards and handed it to me. The other guy took his time placing everything in the bowl so nicely just to have it all mixed in and ugly when I opened it.
First time here and I'm not disappointed with the Rockport.  A different flavor in every bite.

First time here and it was delicious!  I love the idea of a sushi burrito!  My wife ordered the Kodiak and I had the Long Beach.  I highly recommend the LB if you like spicy!

Overall, it was a good experience.  The place is clean and the staff was friendly.  The only reason why it's not 5 star in my book is because of the price.  It is fairly expensive to eat here, so it really is only a "once in a while" treat for us.

I love sushi burritos.  Back in the day I would have to wait for Jogasaki at Foodie Fest or take a trip to Cali to get my fix.  Now they are all over Vegas and I try to check out every spot.  I ordered a Rockport combo with Taro Chips and side of cheese.  Both were fresh and delicious.  Service was very friendly and the line moved quick.  The owner came up and chatted with me about my meal and their new location in the Linq.  I put in my vote for a Henderson location next.  Luckily I work nearby so I can get my fix during the week.

This is my second or third time here - and each time I eat here I think to myself "I should come more often!" 

It's a restaurant, so the rating boils down to two things: food & service. If you've looked at my other reviews you know I don't give out 5 stars frequently, but I just feel like this place consistently exceeds my expectations and has earned it. 

Food: it's sushi so you assume it's super fresh, but that's not always the case. Swing into JaBurritos though and your going to get super fresh and tasty fish. The portions are plentiful and there's no way you'll leave hungry. The flavors are on point and there's a variety of fillings, sauces, and extras that makes your meal "yours." There are plenty of options, but I'm a seaweed wrap guy. Maybe I'll try a bowl, tortilla, or something next time. 

Service: I thought the first time here that I got lucky to have someone who must be an owner or manager helping me, because the service was way to friendly for the type of restaurant (picture Chipotle or Subway, but with sushi / Mexican / Asian inspired fresh & healthy options).  Well - three or four times, visits to both the Rainbow and Linq locations, and everyone has the same great attitude. 

Also important in a restaurant is cleanliness. If the place wasn't clean I wouldn't have stuck around long enough to taste the food or write a review.  So I guess that a review really boils down to 3 things?

Last thing about this place - it's wallet friendly. Usually I can get out of here for under $10 (I'm trying to consume more water) but even adding a couple of bucks for a combo and you'd be pressed to spend more than $12 or $13.

Hope you take the time to stop by and try it. I'd live for them to do well enough to open another shop someplace a little more convenient to me when I'm working. It's a great lunch!

My coworkers and I go to Jaburritos at leaste once per week. The staff is friendly and knows us by name (and they know our orders by heart!). Food is always fresh, delicious and, even though the line looks long around lunchtime, it moves quickly!

Even though Jaburritos is almost identical to Soho Sushiburrito on Sahara Ave, Soho triumphs Jaburrito when it's all said and done.

We came here on a Sunday afternoon for lunch. I always order the Rosarito (aka Firecracker at the Sahara location). But here, the burrito is very bland. And they STILL don't have the Diablo Habanero hot sauce. My spicy tuna wasn't even spicy!!!! What a disappointment!! Their taro chips here were stale. Nacho cheese for the dipping sauce was watery. I wouldn't be surprise if they diluted the cheese with water....just to be cheap and save some bucks. Service was slow. The Sahara location runs like a well-oiled machine. Thought I'd give this location a second chance, but no....I'll be at the Sahara location from now on.

Food: 5 stars. It is so unique and creative. Essentially it's sushi flavor with the sauces and proteins, but has the best parts of Mexican food added. Build your own roll essentially. Very good and very filling. Around $10 will fill you up. 

Customer Service: 3.5 stars. The employees are fantastic. Each one was nice and helpful. Need to pick up their speed though. It was at lunch time, in their defense, but line was to the door. 

Cleanliness: 5 stars. Bathroom was super clean. Floors and seats were clean. Every time someone left their seat, someone would clean up the spot. Excellent! 

I will most definitely be back. The food is great. I love that is new and they do it with perfection. I hope they build more of these locations. If they had one near the college, the line would never be empty as this would be THE spot!
So, so, so good. It's not near me but when I'm in the area I try to stop by. Downside is the rolls aren't cheap, but since I don't get them often I don't mind too much.
Food is good but they keep messing up my orders when I get delivery from them. Something is always missing

Love this place and I don't even eat sushi! They have 2 fabulous meat options which were so flavorful and delicious- they have something for everyone! Perfect location and the friendly staff gets you in and out fast!

I have been wanting to try the famous sushi burrito craze! Coming here was well worth it!! The food is delicious and fresh! The employees are very helpful and patient explaining the whole ordering process! 
Definitely our new healthy place to eat!! 
*The side order of taro chips are a must try!!!*
I love this place been here many times and have never been disappointed. They staff his helpful as there is a greeter that will explain they different varieties / combinations you can have.
I love this place, normally with some sushi places I use heavy extra sauces. This place was fantastic, didn't use any and the flavors are amazing!

Awful customer service / outstanding food
No one greeted.
We stood waiting to order without being acknowledged  the cashier walked away before finishing the transaction she was busy sitting on the back counter to realize the importance of customer service and cleanliness, the floor was a mess with food and menus

however outstanding idea and taste
I ordered the rockport and it was out of control delicous. Spicy and a very large portion definitely fresh ingredients
My wife ordered the Waikiki and she loved it. It was a southwestern style meal and delivered with taste

The reason for 3 stars was the awful customer service there was no follow thru for example they delivered the food and did not ask if we needed anything such as wasabi ginger soy sauce utensils. They absolutely did not care. 
Too bad too because food was excellent. 

According to the receipt Natasha d took our order
We were here 4-9-17 @ 10:31 pm
Someone check the cameras and you will see. 
Fix this and your place would do better we will give it one more try soon because of the food but just an awful customer service experience.

Never tried sushi burritos or bowls before, and it was amzing! I had the long beach bowl with sushi rice and it was delicious. There wasnt a long line, casual seating, food tasted fresh and the prices were good. We will be back!

I've heard so much about sushi burritos recently.  As someone who lives in the middle of nowhere, it's not something I have access to locally so when I found out a couple of spots opened in Vegas I was excited to finally try one.  Jaburritos was absolutely worth the trip to the linq.  I chose to make my own combination, and chose salmon, spicy mustard sauce, cilantro sauce, cream cheese, and crunch.  Delicious!  I'm craving these now which is a shame because there are none nearby.

Today was my second time coming here and it was completely different from the first . The employees were really nice and energetic and gave a good feel for the atmosphere . I decided to order a Long Beach burrito with no guac bc I'm extremely allergic to it . Once I received my burrito I went to snapchat it because who wouldn't ? And I realized that there was guacamole in it . I went up to tell the employees and without hesitation they made me a new burrito free of charge . I felt bad for the inconvenience but they seemed more than happy . Their customer service was amazing and I'm looking forward to coming back .
So good! The ingredients are very fresh . We've been there twice and had different items both times. Everything was delish!

Really dope place and friendly workers that explain the menu in detail. 

I heard about this place from a friend who worked in Vegas. Came here to try it out since I've been obsessed with poké back in Cali. Their burritos are really filling and flavorful. 

I got the Rockport on seaweed paper. It has a spicy taste to it and crunchy with the tempura and the soft shell crab. I always love crunchy texture to my food makes it exciting. 

Past few days I came here, everyone seems so happy when they come to eat. I rarely see that, and the people make conversation with you asking how you which burrito is your favorite. Really dope and cool place. Would recommend

Sushi burrito is now off my bucket list, but I'm sad I'm going back to land without sushi burritos in my life. 

We got in and out really quickly for a Wednesday and there was parking to spare in the lot. 

I settled on the Long Beach in seaweed and also made it into a combo with seaweed salad. 

Mother of God, my mouth was happy. 

The man got a redondo, but in a flour tortilla (he's a newbie, I will forgive him) but it wasn't all bad. I highly recommend the seaweed if your dealing with the more traditional sushi contraptions. 

The whole experience was delicious, filling, a little pricey, but worth it and the staff was pretty nice. 

In the end, it's a thing you must do for yourself and humanity. Buy the sushi burrito, take the nosh... my stolen wisdom for you.

Thankful to have sushi burritos in the southwest! You get to choose from nori, soy paper (it's thin, light-weight, with sprinkles of sesame seeds in it), or tortillas for the burrito. Love the many add-ins to choose from to make your own burrito - I can't believe fish eggs are an option! I love tobiko and masago is a happy substitute.  If you don't want to customize a burrito, though, they have several of their own burritos to pick from that are well-explained on their menu board. If the menu still kinda perplexes you, the friendly, helpful group of workers will guide you. The fish was soft, the sauces were on-point, the veggies fresh - if they keep this up, I can't see why they wouldn't keep customers frequenting this place! Definitely need to return to try the jachos and donburis.

When sushi burritos came out, I wondered why I would want one as opposed to trying a few different rolls at a sushi place. I still would rather have rolls, but this makes a great lunch!

I have only tried one thing here is the Rockport burrito but I've gotten it 3 times. I looooove eel sauce since I have a sweet tooth. I get it with brown rice and without mayo or aoili or whatever cream sauce. I think since it's with brown rice it isn't as amazing as it could be but that is my choice. 

It's a little expensive for any every day type lunch, but I do enjoy it and I should probably try other things! 

Ohhhhh almost forgot my favorite part, the taro chips and Velveeta type queso. So bad, but so damn good!
SO good! You can fully customize your sushi burrito to your specific taste. The fish is really fresh and tastes great!
I don't think I can ever get sick of this place! Whenever I'm in the mood for fast and delicious sushi burritos, this is my go to! Staff is friendly, service is always great, convenience is a plus!

Burritos filled with raw fish and crab meat, taro chips with spicy queso, and a ginger sour cream sauce. Am I taking crazy pills?!

The idea of Jaburritos isn't a new one, but they are delicious alternative to most for the lunch spots in the area. Like a lot of the newer faster paced eateries hitting Vegas, Jaburritos does both the "you create it" or "premade" style or ordering. If it's your first time here go with the premade Jaburrito, it will be a way less stressful especially if a line is forming behind you. Oye, that's too much pressure. 

For the timid sushi eater I suggest going with the Rockport, Malibu, or the Redondo. They are all pretty basic sushi rolls filled with all the inauthentic Japanese goodness that we've come to love in Americanized sushi; imitation crab, shrimp, avocado, cucumber and some type of spicy creamy sauce. The three rolls I mentioned earlier in the review have those basic ingredients give or take some Masago. My personal favorite and repeat order has been the Rockport, its a beats stuffed with Soft Shell crab, Spicy Tuna, Surimi Crab (Crab Paste) Jalapeno, Masago, cucmuber, a tempura crunch and eel sauce. 

Even though this sushi burrito is huge it won't leave feeling bloated and ready for that mid afternoon nappy time. Not feeling the seaweed wrap? Get it wrapped in soy paper, that's my preference too, let's be friends!
I had this for the first time last week...It was delicious. They have a very extensive menu and I can't wait to try it again!

I went to Jaburritos for the first time last night and let me just say that it was the first time I was glad that there was a long line. All the menu items looked so good. There are so many wonderful choices and if, for some strange reason, you couldn't find something to your liking, you can make your own burrito/bowl. It was like a Chipotle for sushi. Anyway, I got the Redondo minus the tortilla and added seaweed salad and sweet chili sauce. The boyfriend got a Rockport as is. I also built a custom burrito for my picky daughter. It was shrimp tempura, seaweed salad, cucumber, and sweet chili sauce. The only reason I gave 4 stars was because one of the girls in the line added tortilla chips when my order specified not to add it. I had to pipe up and ask her not to put them in. She apologized and picked them out. She also forgot the seaweed salad which, by then, I saw that I was holding up the line and didn't feel was a big enough deal. I still got charged for the extra topping, again, not a huge deal since I didn't say anything. All of the burritos tasted amazing. I cannot wait to go back.
I was very excited to see this new location in Las Vegas as it's so much closer for me. The food was fantastic and the staff was kind and a pleasure to be around. I will definitely be back.

Yes - the place is legit.  It's really quite good, and if there is a line when you get there I will tell you that it is worth the wait.  They serve sushi burritos, salads, rice bowls, and nachos.  The burritos can be ordered in seaweed, soy, or flour tortillas (I prefer soy paper).  I've eaten here several times since they opened, and everything has been good so far.  If I'm feeling like I want Japanese, I get the Redondo.  If I'm feeling like I want Mexican, I get the Boardwalk or the Waikiki. I like the beverage options as well, but the best part is the friendly staff.  They chat with you while they prep your meal, and while you sit and eat one of the managers stops by to see how you are doing.  That's a nice touch in a fast casual restaurant, and its one of the reasons that Jaburritos will succeed.  Yes, mid-day traffic on Rainbow is awful, but parking is easy so you should go.

The best sushi burritos on Earth! 

This place is amazing! The freshest ingredients, the best menu and the friendliest staff. 

Stand outs Include the Long Beach, the Kodiak, and the Boardwalk. You can't go wrong here. 

Don't forget to add a miso soup, taro chips w cheese dip, and some mochi!
This was the best fusion burrito I've ever had! The employees go above and beyond to take care of each customer! Loved it and will dream of the next time I eat here.
Great tasting Sushi Burritos and they're huge! Also, I made my order through the Yelp order 24 app. So convenient!

Redondo beach is the first bowl I've tried here. Probably one of many bowls I'll get here. I prefer bowls over the burritos. Redondo beach comes with shrimp tempura, crab, guacamole and spicy tuna

P.s. The green tea mochi ice cream is off the chain!
Staff is great. I've been here several times and it always blows me away. Definitely made it into my rotation of favorite lunch spots.

The long awaited and anticipated visit to the Jaburittos!! I was first introduced to the concept of this kind of sushi when a friend of mine brought me to a place called Soho burrito! I'm wondering if they are affiliated or competitors? Anyways I live super close to this location so I can only imagine this one being my regular go-to for the whole concoction of sushi and burritos! They have pretty similar things as the other place and with this being my first time to the location I wanted to test the staff's knowledge on their menu just to see how much they could tell me. I did plenty research and actually knew what I wanted before ordering however another recommendation could always help sway you to a different item! I love spicy and I also love fish! With THAT being said I went for "the Redondo"! So good! The spicy wasabi mayo sauce is sooo good I even asked for a little extra! I can't wait to go back and try some more! There's about 4 more that I need to get checked off my list and by that time I should even be "a regular"!

Walked in here for the first time today. Was warmly greeted by staff. Nice clean place. I ordered a byob. Prices are decent, portion size was decent. I prefer soho sushi bowlrrito personally because it is a little bit cheaper and portion sizes are better. This place comes to a close second. Will be back occasionally.

I told my mom that they had sushi burritos now and she was excited to give it a go, luckily she loved it! I have tried a sushi burrito in San Francisco, but it fell apart at the seems whereas our Jaburrito's stayed wrapped for smooth eating. We appreciated the Taro Chips, light with a slight kick of spice on them. I will def be back!

We were excited when we heard early this year that Jaburritos was coming to our side of town.  I was watching check ins a couple of days ago and sweet I saw some Yelp buddies checking in to Jaburritos.  I quickly added them as a bookmark and made plans to check them out.  We got down with working out and were starved so it was time for a Sushi Burrito.
   We drove the quick 2 miles to their location and were happy to know they are next to several of our favorite places - Pie Me Over and Rosallie.  What a perfect spot as we can get treats from all of them during our next visit!  The inside was simple and has the feel of not being fully finished.  It was very clean and since it is fast casual not a big thing.  
   We were happy to see they went have the original Jaburritos menu.  Since we had been to Soho Sushi Burritos several times it was confusing to decide which was our favorite.  We had been to the former Jaburritos a couple of times before the name change.  We got the Redondo, Baja, Huntington, Long Beach, and Mission.
   They wall were delicious.  I will say the Baja is hot as the jalapenos are not the mild ones.  Not an issue but a warning for those they don't like the heat from true jalapenos.  The ingredients were all fresh and so tasty.  The fish was very fresh and made the meal perfect.  We all had a moment of Zen as we devoured our sushi burritos.  
   We also ordered the chips and cheese which also came with a surprise.  The cheese was spicy unlike the other location.  Again not a bad thing but something to be aware of if you are not a fan of spicy food.  They only had standard chips but did say Taro chips will be added to the menu soon.
   If you love sushi then Jaburritos is a place you need to visit.  The best thing is you don't have to wait the normal agonizing time to get your delicious food.  You can eat in and quickly be on your way home with your tasty meal.  And if you have a sweet tooth they are in the same building as Rosallie which if you haven't been too will be a perfect dessert to add to your meal.
