A friend turned us on to this place, so glad she did. Menu is interesting, combinations are paired perfectly. A little on the pricey side but well worth it.....

Our favorite sushi burrito place in town!! We live in summerlin and drive all the way there because they're the bomb!! This is a must try place. Great food and staff! Can't say enough good things about this place!
Clean and welcoming environment! Chipotle meets sushi! Fresh ingredients and great tasting combinations! The rockport wrapped in soy paper is my favorite!
I've come here often on my lunch break. The food is consistently good and service is quick, even when there's a line. If you're not sure what to get, the staff is happy to make suggestions.

Just moved into town and I heard about this place! I had the Huntington - consistency was great and the portion are very reasonable! Customer service exceeded my expectations - I was expecting to wait in line but I was in and out faster than expected.
Great service food was prep fresh and organized. I loved the shrimp tempura it's amazing an a burrito

One of my fave sushi burrito places. I like to make my own bowls and burritos, and they have lots of fresh ingredients to choose from. I love the combos they have with their burritos and bowls. Plus if you sign up for the loyalty program you can earn free meals and appetizers. Plus they just opened a location near the linq!

I love sushi, but sushi burrito is just too much. Sushi  has better flavor in small portions. And I still prefer burrito with mexican flavor. For the money i paid, it seems like AYCE sushi is the better deal.

They have vegan steak from Gerdein, and they're always sure to get the order right. Also, they have uberEats, which is great if you're nearby and bored of everything else, which I usually am.  Planning on making this a regular spot for uber delivery.

This review is specifically for the Rockport burrito with Seaweed Paper. I've gotten it twice now and it's super delicious... kinda has spicy sauce but not too spicy. I'm probably going to have to order that same one whenever I go because I like it so much. There are also some of these awesome little crispy thingies.. yum yum!

Great food and very filling... I ordered the Rockport in a brown rice bowl.  I knocked off one start because I ordered the miso soup and it wasn't all that great (I couldn't even finish it), but the bowl was awesome!

Love this place! I have no other sushi burrito place to compare it to, but I get some pretty major cravings for these things. Also, you can get mochi here, and it makes life a little more complete. 

The staff is always friendly and they all seem well trained.

The restaurant is usually a little cold and these large sushi rolls tend to fall apart a little towards the end, but I enjoy these burritos so much that I'm not even going  to take away any stars!

I love Jaburritos. My go-to order is the Long Beach on soy paper, easy on the guac. This is the best place to order online from and run in and get it. Eat at Jaburrito with confidence. It's amazing and filling!

Had to try it out. Didn't get a burrito. It next time I will. It's a cool spot. I got the bowl. Comes with rice, spicy tuna, surmiri crab, tomatoes, avocado, red onions, cucumber, yuzu avocado dressing and spicy mayo. Yup sounds like there is so much but it was just right amout of flavors everywhere. The bowl was $8. Not bad for price. You are paying for raw fish. Since that's what's in now a days. 


The line wasn't so long but there was one. Handful of people but I took my food Togo since I had to pick up the hubs. Place is clean and well kept. Now the next time I'll be trying the Ja Burrito!

Hubby and I passed  this on our way home. We happened to be extremely hungry so we stopped and decided to check this place out. Hubby ordered the long beach and I ordered the Malibu. Service was quite quick and they had our sushi burritos ready in just a few minutes. Both were good but we liked the long beach better. Is it good? Yeah. Would we go back? Eh, maybe if we were around the area.
This place is delicious! If you even remotely like sushi, you must go. Like quick, reasonably priced food packed with flavor? Look no further.

TASTE SO GOOD! I was craving sushi and wanted to try something new! Just as fresh and filling as a sushi roll, not too messy like some burritos, stayed all in once piece for all flavors in all bites. Definitely recommending to others and returning to fulfill my cravings for sushi in the future.

Such a good place to eat! Its fresh and delicious. I got the Waikiki and my fiancé got the long beach. I got the Waikiki in form of a burrito with no queso de gallo, and it's honestly so full of flavors! I would order it again in a heartbeat! The service is great and the staff is friendly. If I had one suggestion, maybe they could have a bigger sized burrito. I know my fiancé could finish two of these babies.
Ive been to a few sushi burritos in town and I think Jaburritos is the best. I met Ken the owner and he was really nice! Great service, high quality fish, and very clean!

With it being my first time at Jaburrito the staff was super friendly and helpful as I had no idea where to even start on the menu. Absolutely loved the Long Beach burrito! I will be ordering the same exact burrito again. I also loved all the different options and how you can make it your own. This place is great for a quick, inexpensive, healthier lunch. Dining in is an option but reminds me more of a grab-and-go type of place. Spacious, clean and environmentally friendly(chairs, napkins, lighting, etc.)

Super stoked when I found out this place was opening down the street from me! I used to go to the one off Sahara and the 15 but it's a little far for me. Overall I was pretty happy with my food. I got the rockport on seaweed. I added seaweed salad and omitted the red onions. My burrito was huge and it didn't fall apart on me! *thumbs up* They also have UCC creamy melon soda which is awesome because normally I can only find it in Chinatown. I'm not a soda drinker but that's the soda I'll drink every once in a great while. 

My only gripe is that there's definitely room for more tables without having everyone bumping elbows. I didn't want to take my food to go but I didn't have much of a choice.
Love the new location !!! Food is excellent and good prices. Definitely recommend this place. My favorite sushi burrito is the redondo.
Amazing! Super friendly staff.  Everything I was hoping it would be! Fresh fish and toppings and super generous portions!

I went here about a week or so after it opened because I was nearby. I expected it to be the same quality as Soho Sushi Burrito on Sahara and it wasn't! I did not like it as much as the selection was limited. I usually order the Mission and add poke sauce on it. The worker who made it overfilled my burrito and it had a lot of items within it. I also add poke sauce to it. However, the staff told me they did not have poke sauce so they made me their own concoction of it. I do appreciate the staff trying to please my requests but it was just not the same. They also did not carry taro chips which is my absolute favorite at Soho Sushi Burrito. I would definitely choose Soho Sushi Burrito over Jaburritos because soho sushi burrito is closer to my home and the quality is better.

Was crazy a sushi burrito although I had never had one but I love sushi so why not?! I went to this location since it was close to work. Chipotle ordering style, I ended up getting the "Long Beach" down with brown rice instead of an actual burrito. and MAN it was SOOOO good and it was a lot of food also so I had the rest the next day for lunch. Staff was very helpful and friendly. Paying was a little crowded and probably was a few minutes of a wait which was weird.  Overall it was great, I am so excited to go back! finally found a good sushi bowl spot!

My first impression when my wife took home the bowl was where is the fish. I wasn't happy primarily because I compared it to some poke shops in California. They're not too generous with their sauces and charge for everything extra you want to add on your bowl. Really had high expectations but it wasn't met. I will try again maybe in a few months.

Hmm.... I honestly cannot figure out how Jaburrito have 4.5 stars. Here is my reasoning:

The food is mediocre. They have some interesting names for their menu items, but that's about it. The ingredients are not as fresh as they should be. The sauces are the simple one that anyone can make at home. There are not that many ingredients to choose from. I think they lack the crucial characteristics that all sushi burritos should have. 

The services is below-average too. The employees were lost half the time. They did mixed up the items among customers. They constantly had to ask each other about what's going on. At least they were nice and friendly.

The interior was simply bad... The entire restaurant seemed unfinished. The interior was just as confusing as the employees.

My overall exeprience was unsatisfying. There are so many sushi burrito/poke places around the area. There is no reason for me to go back to Jaburitto.

Excited about this location opening!! I practically live in the dance studio right next door, being there 5 days a week and we needed some yummy food close by. I've been to their sister location on Sahara and fell in love at first bite. Unfortunately my love for these burritos didn't warrant a drive across town so this was, needless to say, a welcomed surprise when they opened shop so close to home! 

They essentially offer the same items as the Sahara location where you can build your own burrito/bowl or nacho's or order off of their list of yummy creations. I chose the latter both times I visited. First day was the Redondo on soy paper and second day was the Rockport! Holy cow!!! They were both amazing!! The staff is super friendly and make sure you get what you want and offer any extra sauces on the side you might be craving. 

Would love to see them incorporate some sort of frequent customer card. :)

I've already brought a few of my dance parent friends over and now they are all hooked too! Seriously worth trying!!
So good! I ordered the redondo burrito with seaweed and it was delicious. They added a good amount of fish. I will definitely come back

Pretty cool concept. Burrito and sushi combined. I think it is a bit pricey for what it is though and I was still pretty hungry after my meal haha. I had the Redondo and it was like $10.95. I think it is worth trying this because the flavor was pretty good and it tasted fresh. I would probably go back and try something else next time.

There were plenty of parking at this plaza.
Ahhh I love Jaburritos!! This was the first place I tried sushi burritos and it was so good!! Everything fresh and tasty. I always get one of their signature sushi burritos and never lets me down.
I love this place ! When i'm not in the mood to do ayce sushi this is my go-to sushi place. Great quality, the young staff is always super friendly.

I'm so happy that there is a sushi burrito place that isn't too far from my house. This place seems to be pretty popular and everyone has been going there. I've been here a few times and let me first say that it is clean, the staff is very friendly and you could tell that there is a culture and a team here, and that's what I like about it. For people that complain about the staff or just the little things, take a moment to realize and be mindful that the team is working as fast and efficient to make sure you have a good experience and a delicious meal, especially when this place always seems to be busy. At Jaburritos, you could build your own bowl or sushi burrito but I usually just pick from the menu, otherwise I'll take awhile building my own. I have tried the Rockport and Redondo; Rockport is definitely my favorite and go to. I want to try the other sushi burritos the next time I come here. I'll definitely be back!

I love this place! So glad they opened one on the southwest side. Not the highest quality fish but it's easy and tasty. Service is friendly. It's my go to lunch spot when I want something relatively healthy these days.

Was in a pinch for something fast.  I was so busy I didn't get a bit all day.  So glad I stopped here.  It took a little while for me to order from the menu because this was new to me.  However I absolutely loved it.  After ordering my food was made quickly and tasted awesome.  Great place to stop anytime.  Definitely would come back.  Place was clean, staff was friendly, knowledgeable and fast.  Thanks guys!
Always pretty good one of the better sushi burritos in Las Vegas.   The taro chips and queso is really nice

Man this place is delicious!  Their menu is interesting and the food is fresh and tasty.  My husband and I cant get about I of this place.  Sometimes we have to wait a bit on the phone to order but it bas never been an unacceptable amount of time.

So this place is in a typical, nondescript Vegas strip mall, but once you walk in its bright and colorful. The super friendly staff all welcomes you regardless of what they're doing. Everyone there is very welcoming and helpful. It is essentially set up the same way as a Chipotle. 

On the menu they have a few preselected options or build your own. You can get it in a burrito, a bowl or nachos. I've had each way and are all delicious. Have had the Redondo and the Baja but usually prefer to build my own. There are about 10 fish options, chicken, steak and even a Gardein option for vegetarians. The toppings section is really great too with a variety of fresh veggies and homemade sauces. 

This is a place I frequent often and will continue to do so. Everything is fresh and tremendously flavorful. Another bonus is they are very sustainability oriented. Recycled metal chairs, bamboo tables and biodegradable plates, cups and plastic ware. Highly recommend this place.

I have a serious obsession with this place.  At least a few times a month, I have to satisfy the urge and eat at this spot.  Every burrito I have had is delicious. Recently, I tried a bowl for the first time.  BOOM! So good.  The burritos feel a little heavier than the bowls.  I highly recommend giving a bowl a try.  For the burritos, my favorite is the Redondo, hands down.

I don't think it's fair to compare this place to Soho, but if you must, I think Jaburritos stands up to its sister.  The fish is fresh, the ingredients are delicious and the staff is friendly.  If Soho Burrito were closer, I would go there.  Not because it is any better than this place, but because John from Soho is the nicest person on the planet.  The location of Jaburritos is a hop, skip and a jump from me and Soho is a haul.  Overall, I am a big fan of Jaburritos.  There is room enough in this town for two delicious sushi burrito joints.

Interesting concept... im on the fence about it. 

Setup almost like a Chipotle with the assembly line of food. My $10.95 "Long Beach" left me thinking that it wasnt bad and i was satisfied but im not rushing back for another. My $11 could have gone further at a number of places and i think thats what ill likely do next time. I like sushi, so of course i wanted to try this new concept and although its not bad i think id much prefer going and having actual sushi. This is a good way to cure your sushi craving on the cheap, if your not in an ayce mood. Not bad food, the dining room was clean, and the service seemed to be friendly enough.

This is my new favorite spot!!! If you love sushi and being able to eat sushi while driving, then this is the spot! Grab a sushi burrito on the go! The Malibu was really good, excited to try all of them! The people working there are super helpful and knowledgeable. Very friendly environment.
I tried this place for the second time and it was really awesome! Both ja burrito and the ja bowl were delicious! They make it right then and there and  you can custom your order to your preference!

If I could give Jaburritos 10 stars, I would!

I've come in multiple times & they never disappoint. Their workers are always so sweet & helpful, & although there's usually a line, they handle it very well. No longer than a few minutes until it's your turn to order. Not only that, but their burritos are awesome. Some people say that their portions are small, but to me it's pretty filling (probably because I get full easily lol). I've only ever gotten the regular burritos, but I'm excited to try the bowls & everything else they have. 

Incredible service, amazing food, & good portions. Would definitely recommend to anyone who loves sushi.
Always enjoy coming here and getting the Malibu. Satisfies the craving for sushi, while still being just enough food for a regular meal.

The best!!! Love the new location and the Baja is my favorite!! Place is usually busy so give yourself at least an hour to hour and a half if you plan on making a lunch trip (12-1:30) totally worth the wait!!
So excited that they've opened right near my job. Love this place. Everyone is friendly. Malibu roll is awesome! Taro chips are in!

Amazing food! I would say just as delicious as the other sushi burrito place in town. 

If I had to make one suggestion to the owner, get the customer flow down a bit better. Walking in and having a long line weave in and out of tables is a bit awkward. Just designate an ordering flow to make it organized.

Overall verdict: will be back probably next weekend.

Great services and the food is bomb. 
 
I had a really big Redondo burrito with extra avocado! 

Clean spot great music. I love the staff! 

Best spot by far!

This place always has the best customer service! The employees are all super friendly which alone makes this place stand out from the rest. Also love that they use biodegradable plates, cups, etc. Definitely one of my favorites for sushi burritos/poke bowls.

Nom nom nom. 

I've been to Ja Burrito quite a few times since they opened this location. I was excited to see it opening when I went over to Rosallie. 

I've always ordered the bowl with salmon, tempura shrimp, sumiri crab and cucumbers! There's an extra charge for actual avocados so I just put on the avocados at home. I am also in love with the Jachos. I saw another fellow Yelpers picture of Jachos and I knew I needed to get it. My husband always orders the burrito with spicy tuna (too spicy for this girl) and whatever else is in it. 

There are a lot of people working behind the counter so the ordering process goes by pretty quickly. There's a rewards club which I would highly suggest you join if you plan on coming back a lot like myself! Get the house soy sauce too!

Exactly what I always imagined if I could take an amazing sushi roll and eat it before it gets cut into smaller pieces.  I read about the burritos being on the small size and at first I wondered if it would fill me up. But as I finished off my meal I was definitely full and just like eating at a great sushi place I wrestled with ordering more for the flavors and taste, but followed good tummy judgement and stuck with being satisfied,  Everything was very fresh.

Will be back to create more sushi burritos!

Side note, we met the owner's mom- such a sweet lady full of appreciation for those supporting her son.

I ordered the Baja burrito and the fish was good but the rice was unimpressive . Who makes sushi rice as mushy as possible and without vinegar . It felt like a consistency of mashed potatoes. 

The portion size felt unimpressive and the food felt like a mushy hand roll .

These sushi-burrito shops are everywhere and Jaburrito is slightly different from the rest. Jaburrito is heavier on the Mexican side than on the Asian. The toppings are more Mexican and they even have tortillas that you can get instead of the seaweed-rice that you normally see wrapping these things. 
The restaurant is clean and the staff are friendly. 
Stick with the pre-made menu options instead of opting to design your own. It'll end up being the same price!
Loved it!! I work nearby now and it will be my go to place for lunch. Really quick and a great idea for a grab and go meal.

Thank you sushi gods!! It doesn't get any better than a sushi burrito!

I've gone a few times, and there is always a line, which is understandable. The serving size for the fish is great! It's a little pricey, and it doesn't really fill you up. If you're super hungry, I'd opt for an AYCE place because it's about the same price if you get two burritos.

Other than that, delicious food and great customer service!

Burrito size sushi rolls...nuff said!  Friendly staff.  Fair prices.  The sushi burritos are BOMB, the side dishes...not so much.  But it's ok because the burritos are filling enough on their own.  Grab a Rockport burrito and a drink and enjoy the deliciousness.

Went to this place omg this was the best thing ever and they made it to my liking. Definitely going again if I go to Vegas again. The staff was very helpful and very nice. And the prices weren't to high either.

Love this place for a quick cheap sushi fix. The rockport is my fav!! The staff is always friendly. It's pretty much a large sushi roll. You can choose their custom options or create your own bowl/burrito. I think the size of the burrito is fairly priced.

Like Jennifer Z put it, this place IS SO GOOD!
I see it as a Chipotle version of poke. 
Choose your fish. Or not, they have imitation crab and omelettes for those who don't eat fish. Unless you choose one from the $5.95 protein options of spicy tuna, sweet omelette, krab, or sweet shrimp, you'll probably end up paying more for your burrito or bowl then one of their thought-out burritos on the menu. 
Then choose your wrapping. Seaweed and soy paper are more popular. I have yet to see anyone eat theirs in a tortilla. Then top it off with veggies and crispy toppings. Their salsa bar is a little underwhelming, though, as I'm not sure watery salsas go well with these burritos, which are more Japanese than Mexican. I just go with the ginger
Yes, the sizes are a tad smaller than that of SoHo, but I think it's a perfect size: It's just enough to get me full, but not make me uncomfortably so.
Besides being delicious, I really really like that Jaburritos tries to to be eco-friendly. There are recycling bins inside and they use sustainable furniture.
Give them a try!

These are amazing! After my first time here, I came back again 2 days later because I was craving another Jaburrito. And it's such a good deal. I feel like I'm getting more food in my one burrito than I would if I went out to sushi and ordered 3 rolls. I will definitely be a customer for life:)

I've been here 3 times so far and have enjoyed it each time. My first experience was great. The manager ask me if it the first time in & explained the items on the menu. I asked what the most popular items were & chose one. The Long Beach burrito wrapped in seaweed. Excellent! 

Customer service is great & the place is kept very clean.

First timer with my co workers. Went for our weekly lunch date and had been wanting to try this place. We were not disappointed. Host greets you and explains the process of you've never been there. My co workers got sea weed burritos. They were awesome. I got the Malibu Jachos. Amazing! Lol I was skeptical at first (especially cause I was a little hungover) Bc I love me my nachos but this was awesome! Will come back! If you get nachos ask for the ginger sour cream. I know it sounds funny but if you've never been to a place like this it all kinda sounds funny. Will be back. But take note come on a warm day. Nothing like a seaweed burrito to cool you down. We came on a rainy day and just stayed cold. The inside is pretty chilly as well probably Bc of the raw fish.

A tale of 2 sushi burrito locations splitting up and opening their own place; it's about comparing the newly divorced parents' homes. 

Pros:
This location is soooo much more convenient than the other one. They are cleaner here, where the other one is filthy...as in don't look at that messy pile on the floor.

Cons:
The rice is too mushy and doesn't bind the burrito well. The protein fillings are bland. They don't have a screaming orgasm sauce (EVERY SUSHI place NEEDS screaming O sauce). The taro chips (now offered) are too thick with some being greasy and undercooked.

I'm not sure why they need 7 people working a short line and a seemingly oblivious guy working the cash register.

Hopefully with time and a more trained staff, this not SO HOt location will get better.
The staff was friendly but I wasn't impressed with the burrito. It was good but not GREAT. I did like the Mexican mixed with sushi vibe... berry creative. Might give it another try.. might not. So so

So freaking yummy! 

Uncut rolls? It has to be Jaburrito!

This was only my second japanese-style burrito place I've ever tried but i loved Nori (the one on Sahara) due to the crunchy goodness. But here, the rice stayed inside unlike the other burrito place on Sahara. Nori was hard to chew, and the rice fell out with every bite.

This place

Expensive for a small amount of food!!! I ordered the Redondo in the burrito.....$11.85 including tax....small portion for a big price. Tasted ok but not the freshest. This place is not worth it for me. Sweet Poke is a better option.
Think of Chipotle but with Japanese food. I really liked this place. The menu isn't as user friendly as Chipotle but if you're not a moron you're able to figure it out.

Raniel is the man!  This guy's customer service skills are off the charts!  The food is bomb squad, too!  I ordered the Redondo Bowl: Spicy Tuna, Shrimp Tempura, and a bunch of other goodies.  I highly recommend this place to anyone looking for high-quality ingredients and friendly and speedy service.
I like the concept but not my favorite. Friendly staff but kinda slow for a lunch time visit.

Love the food, hate the service. 

I go in and order a Baja and it usually has a decent amount of fish in it and the guy ahead of my complains and gets more meat on his and the chick behind me of course the d!ck bag behind the corner hooks her up without even flinching or batting an eye like he did on both my proteins. Biased fuck!

Yay for sushi burritos in the south west! Now I don't have to drive across town to get to their sister location.

Fantastic food and very friendly staff. This location is larger than their sister location so they have a bit more seating.

If you like more traditional sushi, go with the Redondo. I'm salivating just thinking about it!
Always love Jaburritos. The concept of the sushi burrito is pretty cool. I also like their taro chips.

My only issue was that the tofu was all at the bottom of the miso soup, but that's nothing important compared to the excellent service, quality food, and tidy restaurant. The employees here clearly care about the service they're providing. 10/10, You get exactly what you're expecting- but in a good way.

I asked my dad where he wanted to go for Father's Day and his immediate response was sushi burritos. Not what I was expecting to hear but I was 100% for the idea. My mom, dad, brother, sister in law and I all came in on a Saturday around 12:30 and there was no wait at all. 

I chose to go with the Redondo and added avocado rather then tortilla strips. Major ordering remorse because once I got mine it had waaaay to much wasabi for my likely and I could barely eat it. Luckily my sister in law traded me for the other half of her Rockport which was a much better choice. Next time I'll keep away from anything with spice.

Besides bad ordering on my part I did enjoy this place. I like that you have the option for combos that come with either seaweed salad, edamame, miso soup or taro chips. It's still very similar to Soho Sushi Burrito but a little bigger inside. I'm sure I'll be back again when I'm towards this side of town.

Very tasty. The staff selections were all delicious. I had the Laguna. Yummy. My wife had the Rockport. Good, a bit on the spicy side, but heat lovers would probably love it. Everyone in the group agreed the burritos were winners. The sides, though, not so much. Seaweed salad and miso were misses. Overall: would definitely go back.

I love Jaburritos! Everything here is top notch- always fresh and delicious. Never that fishy smell or taste from not-so-fresh sushi. They really care about their ingredients. 

Everyone working there is awesome too. Every time I come in they are all bubbly, everyone has a smile on their face, and no one is ever too busy to welcome you when you enter. I love this place and will definitely be back!

Jaburritos is always a good option when you're craving a sushi burrito. The service is typically great every time I've gone here. The employees are quick to help when you walk in.

My go to order is a Long Beach burrito. It's the perfect blend of spicy and crunchy! It's spicy tuna, shrimp tempura, surimi crab, romaine lettuce, cucumber, tortilla chips, guacamole, chipotle mayo, & sweet anguilla sauce.  

My only flaw in Jaburritos is their online ordering option, I used uber eats to order a Long Beach. I didn't know how the system worked to order, I assumed once I selected the Long Beach that all the options that are in the burrito were already selected. Turns out that you have to select the options you want in the burrito and any addition options as well. I thought that was a minor flaw. When I got my order I found that the only items that were in my burrito were the ones I selected, I thought the options I selected would be added to the included ingredients. Also the sweet Anguilla sauce wasn't an option to select so you have to side note it. 

Other than the uber eats order flaw, I love Jaburritos. One burrito is enough to fill me up, if I'm feeling super hungry I'll get a combo with taro chips & queso.

Had a flour burrito, white sticky rice, steak, shrimp tempura, avocado cilantro dressing, wasabi mayo, cabbage, bell pepper, corn, cilantro with some soy sauce on the side... omg soooo good! Chips and Queso were whatever, the flavor was boring, but the burrito was on point. The staff is super friendly and helpful. It was my first time there and they let me try a few of the sauces to see which one I liked. Really enjoyed this pleace, will definitely be going back!
This place is so good. I was a huge fan of Soho Sushi burrito till I tried this place.  They always get my order right and it tastes amazing.  Definitely try it you won't regret it
Tasty, healthy and something different. Great food and cool stuff. Thanks guys.  I recommend this place. 5 stars from me...

Way to overcome grand opening jitters! I've gone back to Jaburritos at least four times since my initial visit and review. And I've got to commend the entire staff on providing an amazing atmosphere to dine in at! From offering personal twists to menu items to remembering me by name... I could go on forever about how warm, friendly, organized and dedicated the entire team is. Management, you're doing EVERYTHING right.

Got the Acapulco.  This place is amazing.  Japanese/Mexican.  This place is one of a kind.  It's fresh and clean food.  I recommend this for any crossfitters.  This place is so good.  Calling all foodies here!

My friend from class invited me to come here to check it out. I was a little iffy at first just because it's a sushi burrito. But I'm like "why not!" 
Came in here and we were greeted by their friendly staff. One of them suggested for me to try the Redondo Sushi Burrito. AND LET ME TELL YOU, that burrito did not disappoint :D it was full of flavor and the fish tasted fresh! The only downfall is the price. In my opinion, it's too pricey since there's not much fish inside compared to the ratio to the rice. But overall, I'm pretty pleased with my meal. I partnered it with Calpico. 
Oh! Don't forget to sign up for their free rewards card ;)

Obsessed!! The Long Beach is my favorite and has been for some time. I just replace the chipotle sauce with spicy mayo and I'm in heaven. drink options are great too. I enjoy the iced coffee in a can, it's soooo yummy! this place rocks and I'm so happy it's open till at least 9pm

I have eaten here twice, and I am not a real big sushi person, so I do not know a lot about it. But, Raniel, and the staff there are very helpful, so I have had two good experiences. I tried the Malibu, without the mayo, add some mango teriyaki sauce instead. Really liked it, and so did my daughter. Will be back!!  Good food, GREAT SERVICE Raniel!! (hope I spelled your name correct!)
Love the service and the people . Food is amazing  I couldn't be any happier for it being in the spring valley area ! 10000x better than the soho location
Amazing! Looks like a burrito but taste like sushi. Damn that was good! I want to come back and try them all. I loved how they have fused the two together and made it into 1 fabulous meal.

Really wanted to like this place, but was disappointed. We had to get in for the sushi cupcakes and a burrito. We got our food pics, but unfortunately, good pics is all we walked away with. To be fair, I saved half of my Acapulco burrito for home and ate it out of the fridge a few hours later. It tasted better than it did at the restaurant. The cupcakes are a very cool concept, and were decorated nicely -love the cupcake to go box- but needs some improvement. Wasn't impressed with the look or feel of the restaurant itself, but would recommend that you try it for yourself.

New post:
The manager of JaBurritos earned the 2 extra stars.  We ended up eating on the patio near Rosalie Cafe.  The cashier must have relayed our feedback right away because within 5 mins, the manager came out to apologize for the smell and acknowledged it is the shortcoming of the building during winter time where the ventilation is poor.  He gave us 4 individually wrapped ice cream mochi's and was sincerely trying to salvage our experience.  Fast forward 5-7mins later, manager came out again to offer to comp our next meal after he got a notification on my Yelp review (which was posted immediately after we ordered and before we received our food.)  To be clear, when he came out the first time, he didn't know about my posted Yelp review.  We are impressed with how much attention he gives to ensure customer satisfaction.  Again, the food is good here but my experience and appetitie was largely affected by a building issue, and not the taste/price/or service.

Original post (2 Stars):
Smells so fishy in here .. like the seafood department of an Asian grocery store.  The original JaBurrito near Charleston UMC, now caled SOHO Burrito doesn't have the bad smell and it's the same menu / price.  Just 5 mins in there and my hair / clothes picked up the odor.  The cashier said it's probably from when they fry the unagi (eel) because it smells bad like that every time the kitchen cooks it.  

We ordered it to go to sit in our car to eat it since we can't stand the nauseating greasy and fishy smell.  I would check out Poke Puku down a few more blocks or SOHO Sushi Burritos off Jones & 215 instead of this location since ventilation isn't something that would get fixed by an owner unless required by law.
Bomb place for sushi burritos , the rolls can be small and you really have to know what sauces you like !

I'm glad they moved closer to where I live and right next door to a French cafe we also like. This was our first visit to this location, we've been to the one in Sahara. I don't know if that one is still open. 

But this time I thought the food was a bit bland. I'm glad I got the soy sauce with wasabi and the pickled ginger. We will try something else next time.

I like the idea.. But it wasn't my favorite or what I ordered wasn't the best. I'm willing to give it another go and hopefully make a better order.
The people are super joyful and helpful and seem to love their job. That was cool.

Just got into Vegas and this was starving, saw Jaburrito and decided to give it a try. I had the Rockport bowl and was not disappointed. This is one of the best Mexican/Asian fusion place. Everything was tasty and fresh. Staff was super friendly. I will def be back.

I'm so happy they opened up by my office.  I had to drive all the way over to their other store for my sushi burrito fix before.    Problem solved now plus for some reason the food is so much better at this location.   The lines are always long but they move fast.  Hopefully they open in summerlin soon too!

I've been looking for a spot I can get a brown rice bowl from and this spot is perfect for it.  I use Uber Eats quite a bit to order from here and that's pretty simple too.  Great food and very affordable for the quality!
Nice twist on a burrito - with rolled sushi. Try the house rolls to start. Quick lunch.

Ja,  this is a great place for a fusion of Japanese with a sort of not Mexican but more of a California Twist

1. The food - These are burrito or bowl type choices in the genre of Chipotle.  You get to pick all the wraps and the protein, sauces and toppings.

2.  The choices - They have here about 12 burritos that are set in a menu preselected with ingredients.  For the uninitiated where choosing everything can be a bit much, these 12 choices are very good. I won't go into the details as you can go to their website and see all the choices and flavors.  The good news is that they are all pretty good.  I find that it is a bit difficult to really differentiate the taste of each one as when you meld everything together and with the sauces, the flavors are a bit fused.

3.  Do it yourself - You can certainly look at all the individual proteins, wraps, sauces and toppings and create your own burrito or bowl. You can order double protein and or mix/match the protein.

4.  The wraps - Flour, wheat, seaweed, soy paper are the different kind of wraps that you can use for your burrito.  You can use brown rice or white rice too!

5.  The combo - When you order your burrito or bowl, you can also order it as a combo with a drink and either Miso, Edamame, Corn Chips, Taro Chips.  The Taro chips are sprinkled with Furikake and both chips come with a queso sauce that is pretty good.

6.  Vegan - If you are a vegetarian or vegan, you can order gardien tofu and set up your burrito or bowl to be completely vegan.  

GK says, check it out.  Pretty fun, different and new to try.  I cannot say that the flavor is out of this world, as it is truly hard when there is so much sauce, however, it is FUN to try and tastes good overall

Sushi burritos is a new thing on my radar...and I really wanted to try this place because they have the most eye catching pictures on Instagram. Going there with the expectations to be served a dish like the one I saw on Instagram was my mistake. Now...don't get me wrong. The food did taste pretty good! It was just not as appealing as what I had seen in pictures. 

The sushi burrito per se is big enough for one person. I ordered the nachos too but was a bit disappointed to see that the chips come from a bag. They are not made there in store...at least they did not taste like they were. 

Another thing that caught me by surprised is that I thought this would be more of a restaurant type. The place is more set up as a fast food joint. Overall the food was good but not a place I would drive out of my way to come visit.

This was my first time trying a sushi burrito and I had heard good things about this place. They lived up to their reputation. It was so fresh and delicious and packed full of fish. Definitely going back to this place.

This place is pretty good size compare to other sushi burrito place in town, plenty of tables and chairs, get the Baja, portion is kind of small, taste average, the salmon bowl with brown rice is ok, nothing special, would rather go back to Soho sushi bowlrrito...

The restaurant is set up like a Chipotle. But I was told to stick with the pre-made menu otherwise the flavors would be off. This was my first visit and I did as directed. The staff was very helpful!!!  I  had the Kodiak and it was very good. The sauces that were on the burrito were blended perfectly. The fresh veggies were refreshing. I put it on a tortilla as suggested because the salmon on my burrito wasn't raw and the seaweed wrap is better for raw fish. Very helpful to know this for future visits.  For a couple bucks more, you get a drink and side. The burrito was perfect and the right price. Not sure I had salmon on my burrito but the fish tasted fine. I will go back.

Ja-On To Something...

I was pretty stoked to try this place because like many I'm a sushi junky. I walked in blind and there were plenty indecisive people like myself trying to figure out what to order. After a short debate I went with the "ROCKPORT" and it was an excellent choice! Just the right amount of spicy, fresh and delish!!!!

I would definitely return in the near future. My only gripe was the staff. I assume this restaurant is new which is awesome and the concept it great but the staff should be a lot more confident. I asked for my burrito wrapped with seaweed and the two employees seemed very confused and kept conversing amongst each other before preparing my order. I ordered one mochie and a young man at the register rang me up for two and asked me literally four times which dessert I ordered. Practice definitely makes perfect and I suspect the staff will get better over time. 

Good Luck

We have heard of this place and wanted to try, but it was always too far.  Now, they are super close and we were able to indulge in their amazing foods.  I was a little hesitant to try it because I know it has raw fish, and my wife is pregnant.  Fortunately, they do have things on their menu that is fully cooked. We are going to be back and recommend this place to anyone who wants to try something different and satisfy your taste buds.

Jaburritos is amazing! Great service and delish burritos!!! For the price, the value is amazing!! I enjoy every burrito when I go!!! I took my co-worker and she loved it too! It's clean and the staff are super friendly and helpful if you aren't sure on what to order. This is my guilty pleasure!!!

Delicious, just frickin perfect. I hesitated trying a sushi burrito since a friend complained that other places put too much rice.  Not here!   A perfect balance of fish, wontons, sauce, and rice. 


Can't wait to return!
I enjoyed my lunch here and felt even better that they have a very strong stance on environmental issues which is as important to me as the food tastes,  which happily was awesome.

Very unique and delicious! 
It's sort of like a huge hand roll, but yeah I guess it could be a burrito. It was delicious and very fresh. But somehow I'm concerned about the sanitation. I guess because it's open kitchen like Chipotle, but Jaburritos is sushi (raw fish) instead of cooked meats. I think it's a healthy food and could be good for lunch and quick grab for dinner. Again, it's HUMONGOUS! And delicious too!

This place is so good. I'm really excited that they have another location with such great prices. I got the Redondo and Rockport Barito which were amazing and made in a timely manner.

The facility is very clean and has very awesome and interactive employees which made the experience super great! They were all very nice cute and funny! I'm so glad this place is down the street from my house so I can come here all the time and spend all of my money. Best of all their food is made with such fresh ingredients and it is truly highest of quality!

I also love that they customize all of your food from soy paper to seaweed! If you don't want to sushi burrito you can get a bowl instead which I think is cool or make your own burrito! Thanks jaburrito for making my wallet happy and my tummy full! You're the best

Btw: the soy sauce is horrible, it was a jelly consistency and salty!
I have been coming here for a while. Food is always awesome. Fish always fresh. Employees have great customer service.

I have not had the chance to eat here yet but the food looks great!
Great presentation

I don't know how new this place is, but I was surprised at how many people were behind the small counter. I think it was 6.  They were definitely training. Everyone was really nice.  The menu board is simple and I chose the rodondo burrito with seaweed paper.  It was $10.75 I think.  and I got a side of seaweed sald for $1.50 I think.  The restaurant was actually a little busy. The inside was really nice looking and clean as well.  Before leaving I made sure to get some of their soy sauce (which was in a pump). I got home and opened up my order, it looked really good and tasted very good as well.  Their soy sauce was not soy sauce though, it was a little thicker and more like a terriyaki glaze. But it was still very good.  As far as food quality, I'd definitely go back. I think everything I had was very very good.  I just felt the portion size was a bit small.  Either lower the price just a little bit or make the burritos a little bigger. It was definitely filling if you want a light-med lunch, but for dinner by itself was not nearly enough and buying 2 which would've been approx $20 is not worth it.  So yea, I'd definitely go for lunch but just not for dinner.  All in all, very good place just need to either adjust the price a little or make it bigger.

This place is so amazingly delicious! They have so many combinations for a sushi burrito or a sushi bowl. They also have some standard bowls that are very yummy. Pretty fresh ingredients!  I recommend knowing what you want ahead of time though, it gets a little overwhelming when you're trying to order. It's a very fast paced assembly line with a ton of different people trying to create your burrito. The kids working behind the counter aren't always helpful either. The food is still pretty good though I definitely recommend trying this place out!

It took me three hours to walk there and it was well worth it. 
Not only did they let me stay after closing time to eat, they had given me a discount for the food, and gave me a ride home when the uber didn't show up. 

Best costumer service I've ever had. 
I would have happily given a hundred dollar tip if I had that kind of money.
The burritos are always delicious with fresh ingredients and the staff is super sweet! Rockport add yellowtail is my go to!
Better than others, smaller rolls than some. Loved their combo meals. They even kept the mochi for us until we were done eating!.

I continue to eat this place at least once a week now that it's by my house. The greatest thing about this place is that although you may be hungry to eat sushi you ask yourself if you're able to do All you can eat and for me most of the time is no. I'm actually able to just go here and grab a sushi burrito. Great idea and it's super quick and easy. I will be spending my hard earned money to come to this establishment for years to come. Love Jaburritos!

My faves are....
Rock port
Long Beach 
Kona Bay
Redondo 


Oh btw Taro Chips are money

My husband and I went today for dinner and I was so happy that they offered so many options. It's a great sushi fix at an even better price! We both got the Huntington and I have never been so happy eating at a new place. I found everything to be delicious and more then filling.

I found the staff to be very helpful and more then willing to add more sauces or whatever was needed. Unlike what others had to say our burritos were wrapped perfectly and stayed that way to the very end. We along with everyone that entered after us, got a very happy hello by everyone. I really can't wait to go back and try more.

I had one in SF and wasn't a huge fan but thought I would give this fusion a chance. Usually I am not a huge fan of fusion but boy did I love this sushi burrito and it wasn't even "Vegas strip" price. It was $10 before tax and tip. I am a fan. I loved the crunch and customization.

I love jaburritos!!!!!!!!!! This place is awesome !!!! And delicious!!!!!! It isn't super expensive and they always have great customer service!! They always have a smile and greet you at the door! I also love that they let you customize your burrito!
Hungry for Japanese Sushi & Burrito too 2. I had to pic JaBurritos. Hehe. Happy Camper!

Super delicious sushi burrito! I was a little weirded out that it's mixing Mexican and Asian food together, but I'm glad I tried this place. I got the Long Beach and my friend got the Rockport. We both loved ours. It's packed with great flavor and tastes fresh! It's definitely worth trying.
Cute place, but the WORST food ever. Raw tuna is horrible, fishy smell, NOT sushi grade, inedible! Would never recommend Jaburrito. Not Good at all....

I fell in love with this place!!!! I recently got into the trend of sushi burritos trying every place in town and wanted to try this spot out.

Once you walk in, you are greeted by the whole staff. They did an amazing job explaining how it works. I ordered the Redondo and was amazed of the quality of the sushi. Great color and texture while the condiments of cucumber,chips,wasabi mayo,red onion, and masago. I love how the burrito was made and wrapped. One side was ahi tuna, the other side was yellow tail, and the middle was salmon. I believe this spot pulls ahead of their competition because they don't drench the sushi with excessive sauce like other places; because they want you to taste the quality of the fish and not mask it.

Also, quality control was AMAZING. As I was ordering, an associate was checking each insert to make sure it was in the correct temperature. On top of that, each and every associate was doing something on their down time. Restocking,cleaning,building burritos, etc. All with a smile. 

Jaburrito takes the top pick in my book for Sushi Burritos
Fast, Quality, and Great Environment
Delicious, and a great value.  I always get the Baja on seaweed, it's killer.

One of my favorite places. It is never disappointing. Who ever came up with the concept of a burrito size sushi roll is a genius!  My husband had a poke bowl with spicy ahi, ahi tuna, soft shell crab and toppings. I stuck to my usual poke burrito with spicy ahi and shrimp tempura with wakame seaweed. As usual the food was packed with many flavors and so delicious!  We topped it all off with sushi cupcakes, which was good but as good as the sushi burrito.  We are definitely fans of Jaburrito!

Ordered delivery service and it arrived quicker than the estimated time I was given! .  I had the soft shell crab flour tortilla burrito and it was delicious. My husband had the Baja burrito and loved it.  Will be ordering from here again soon.

Staff was really
Friendly and the food was great. Custom made a roll and there are tons of sauce and veggie choices- really yummy!
This place was delicious, I'm not too crazy about tortilla chips in my sushi so I got one without and it was so good! Will definitely be back

First time at a sushi burrito place..

Not a bad idea and an interesting concept but I opted out of the burrito and went with a bowl style lunch from here.

I ordered the spicy tuna bowl with white rice. Quality was good, fish was fresh, flavors were there but that's really not that hard to achieve if you just keep to the simple basics and do it properly.

The location isn't terrible it's in a small shopping center with minimal parking so I'm certain when the plaza is busy find a spot to eat here might pose as a problem.

Inside was clean and well kept by the 9 employees that are working behind the counter. Ordering, preparation and paying was a breeze. I definitely will return to try some of there other offerings

I will be back.  had the baja burrito on nori.  Wow was it good.  Great flavor from the spicy tuna, but could also taste the yellowtail.  The tortilla strips added a nice crunch and the Avocado Cilantro Sauce is great.

The staff is very friendly and helpful.

I am not sure what I would do differently.

Honestly not the best price to get sushi burritos. They are done pretty well but I had to buy here since I work close. My main complaint is just that almost everything is extra price and if you do get them they dont put a lot on the roll.

This is a great alternative to spending 65/70$ for sushi. One JABurrito is like eating 3 rolls. It's delicious and you can tell they use quality products.  They have a little salsa bar but soy sauce does the trick. We will definitely be back this is our new spot for when we are craving sushi but are on a budget. 

We had the Long Beach, comes with spicy tuna, tempura shrimp , surimi crab, a spicy mayo, eel sauce, cucumber, tortilla strips, guacamole & lettuce. ( I could have done without the lettuce but it's what makes it a burrito) mmmmmm

Wow! Asian and Mexican get married and have JaBurrito babies and they are beautiful!
Excellent quality food uniquely paired well. We thoroughly enjoyed the Boardwalk and the Malibu. 

The Boardwalk was like a Philly cheese steak elevated into a savory sushi roll. So satisfying. 

The Malibu on soy paper was like a fresh crab salad, cucumber crunchy, fresh, delightful and elevated with pickled ginger and wasabi. SO GOOD!
Highly recommend the in house made Taro chips! We are so glad the delightful gentlemen who helped us recommended them. Staff was super friendly, helpful and engaging. 

This is a special place not to be missed if you are looking for a fun and delicious foodie experience. 
And a major plus is they make everything in house and do not use MSG.

This place is awsome!  The redondo burrito is packed full of sushi and the seaweed salad is spot on.  My wife got the Waikiki Bowl and miso soup and thought both were incredible. This will be at least a weekly stop.
This place is amazing! I got the Redondo with a side of seaweed salad and my mouth is tingling in the best way possible. I highly recommend Jaburritos to anyone who like food with flavor.
I read a lot of good reviews about this place so I had to try it for myself. It was good but nothing really exceptional about the food. The staff were great and really friendly.

How can you not give 5 stars to a burrito sized sushi roll? lol 

This place is very casual but so cute. You place your order and pay at the counter and the dining room has open seating/first come first seated. The staff was attentive and eager to help with suggestions and questions.

I had the Redondo Roll but substituted the cilantro and jalapenos with lettuce and cucumbers and it was DELICIOUS! I look forward to coming back to try more flavors.

Found this lil gem on Yelp while searching for a quick lunch.  Neither of us had heard of it before, so we rolled the dice, and came out winners!!

Small, quick, and quality food.  What more could you ask for!?  

If you're unfamiliar with Jaburrito, as we were, I'll fill you in..  

We were greeted at the door by one of the partners of the business, door being held open for us, shuttled to where the line is to order food.  Kind of like those other burrito places where you order the burrito and they build it in front of you, but with sushi style ingredients and some fusion ingredients.  I ordered the Kodak, a salmon based Jaburrito, with the wheat wrap, Options of wraps being seaweed, rice, tortilla, or wheat.  The salmon wrap was excellent!!  And I ordered the combo with seaweed salad as my side.  A great lunch overall. 
Jaburrito also emphasizes their use of eco friendly products and building systems, maybe shooting for a LEED rating, which is admirable, in my opinion and another reason to support this business.  The food alone has my business.  Highly recommend.
I got a revuelto salad. It was very fulfilling and delicious. The service was ok. They didn't smile much, but they were very nice and understanding when I forgot my debit card and had to comeback.

I am really digging this new concept of fusion of foods. In this case, it's Japenese and Mexican, thus a sushi burrito. 

I ordered: a custom sushi burrito: 
Protein-spicy tuna and shrimp tempura
Wrapping-soy paper
Rice-white
Sauce-cilantro avocado yuzu and sweet eel
Addings-seaweed salad and tempura flakes

I would order the same exact burrito again. Imagine a poke bowl in a burrito. I've had Sushirito in San Francisco and I give them 4/5 stars just because their ingredients seem tastier and because they are the OG's when it comes to this sushi burrito craze. 

This place is great for a quick, relatively inexpensive lunch. Service is decent and the place is clean.

Upon walking in, I'm always greeted by the entire staff. It makes me feel great to the point where I want to order 10 jaburritos. The place is clean and small, not too crowded though. The first time I ever visited, the staff explained to me step by step how to order my Jaburrito, now I consider myself a professional Jaburrito orderer. I LOVE that I can order on their APP and pick it up before work. AND NOW, I get POINTS for checking in.

The food is delicious. I usually get the Rockport rolled inside a sushi wrapper. It contains all fresh ingredients including soft shell crab, surimii crab, tuna, jalapenos, cucumbers, tempura crunch and chipotle mayo. I usually hold the red onions! If you want to try sushi burritos, this is a GREAT non-intimidating PLACE to start. The pricing is on point too, about 7 to 11 dollars for this big sushi burrito. I love it.
Was reluctant at first, but yeah that's some good eats. Nice size, good price. The order taker was very nice and explained everything.

So I'm not sure about the origin of Jaburrito but the first one I originally went to was located on Sahara. (Which is now the amazing Sohosushi Burrito) I don't know if this is the same company but if it is you would never be able to guess affiliation by tasting the food here. My husband and I ordered 3 burritos. I was disappointed in all 3. No flavor even with the sauces. Very bland and one burrito was like a bootleg "3 amigos" from Soho Burrito. Not my cup of tea and with all of the new sushi burrito spots opening they need to step their game up.

my kids love this place. personally, can I have a suggestion for the restaurant? is it possible to have all the counter food servers to wear a mask to cover their mouths? when they made the food, some of them were talking talking. u know what I mean?
The service was great and the food as well.  I wish they had more Vegan options like other Sushi Burrito places have.

Wow, I am definitely surprised! I didn't think I would like this concept, but I love Jaburrito! Also thanks to the awesome cashier Andre for the recommendation! Will be going back to try every single burrito for sure!

Great service. Love coming here during my lunch break and never had a problem with overcrowding and finding a table to sit at. Their sushi quality tastes great and the price is reasonable for the portions. Gotta say, their bowls could be a little taller or wider. It's a bit of a struggle to stir it around without overflowing and making a mess!

Los Angeles got me addicted to sushi burritos like 5 yrs ago from this food truck Jogasaki Sushi Burritos. I was obsessed and then it became a phase. But now that phase is back and I'm ready for it here in Vegas. 

Felt like sushi and referred to my Yelp bookmarks and realized Jaburritos was on my list. So glad it was. 

Everyone was super friendly and helpful given it was my first time and I needed a moment. Had salmon and tuna in a seaweed wrapper burrito. Great suggestions with the sauces of ponzu and a new spicy mayo. You can add whatever other additions you would like as well like seaweed salad, jalapeños, green onion... The burrito was so satisfying and all for the small price of 7.99 including the 2 fish and avocado. You can't get a roll that big and delicious for 7.99 at a sushi restaurant. 

Other options include nacho style over chips or a bowl over rice which I think I'll do next time.
While in Vegas we stopped here for a quick bite! I tried the Long Beach it was amazing. The next day we went back for more just to take on the plane!! OMG SOOO GOOD! A must try whenever in Vegas!!

This place was like chipotle for sushi!!! Food and service was good! I made my own burrito with extra toppings and it was only around $10 which is a fair price because you get more food than if you were to order just a long roll. Before the only way to get sushi burritos in vegas was if you went to foodie fest so im glad this opened! I couldn't think of a reason not to give it 5 stars

First time was with my good friend and I got Redondo based off what he got. The burrito is a good size, but keep in mind this is coming from a person who couldn't even finish the burrito. 

I've only gotten these 3 on the numerous times I've visited. 

Redondo - hands down winner. only get this now. 
Huntington - only ordered this once, nothing special 
Baja - only ordered this once, nothing special 

Let me tell you, get the bowl! More food. And opt for salad instead of rice if you want to eat healthier/conscious of diet. 

I come here super often, especially since I work down the street, but it's only 4 stars because the staff is slow so when there's a long line, beware. They may not be used to it or they just naturally can't keep up but every time I'm here I know it's not going to be a quick "get my food get out" thing. 

I hear they also just incorporated online (their website)?and app (chownow) ordering so that may be a good solution for people (like me) that always order to-go.

I don't know what I was expecting, because it's just an over stuffed sushi roll. With that said, it's super delicious! I had the redondo and substituted the wasabi mayo for the chipotle mayo and it was AMAZING! They had a few of other options that Ill come back and try.

The service was a bit slow considering it wasn't that busy. Everyone seemed overwhelmed, but friendly. They need to get organized.

Been here several times and they do not disappoint! Tried others but always come back to JaBurrito. I always make a point in trying different ones but so far the Redondo is one of my favorites but you can always customize your meal too- staff is always friendly and make a point at stopping at your table to make sure everthing is to your liking.

How had I not tried this sooner??!? All I have to say is: YUMMY. How refreshing! How clever! How tasty!! The fish was SO fresh. The rice perfectly cooked. And the flavors explosive. I had the Redondo with all fresh salmon and it was literally *perfection*. Get here quick if you haven't tried it yet!

My new favorite place!!! Excellent customer service!!  The lady in the front, the one that takes your order is amazing! She took time to explain and make sure we were happy with our order. We order the kodak and the Long beach, they were so good!! Fresh and delicious!!

A very long over due review. 

For what they are putting down, making. The food is great. Yummy. Fresh and you are able to substitute when needed. Extras may cost some $. But never much. It is much better than getting those pre-made sushi sold in stores to get your sushi fix for less money than going to get sushi at your favorite place. Quick. Easy. Good.  

I like it and whenever I can I will go. Push throw time traffic and get a sushi burrito. Yum. Sometimes it's hard just to get one or for you not to eat it all before getting home.  It's that good to me. Like the variety of items that go into their specialty rolls 

Of course it's not that high quality sushi. Affordable. And not Hawaiian grade poki or anything but close enough for Vegas. 

PS. The customer service I receive is always on point. I can and am very social and just like in Hawaii, love to chat it up. All the employees who have helped me are nice friendly and quick to make your order. 

They also have a rewards program of some sort (can't quite remember all of it) but they will explain and help you out with it if you ask them. Also get email discount and with yelp you can also get cash back when registering your card.

I've been seeing these sushi burritos all over my Yelp feed from various people in California, Las Vegas, and Hawaii.  What's the hype?  It's just a giant sushi roll, right?  Oh. Mah. Gawd. Can we open a Jaburritos in Arizona because wow cow!

We ordered a Rockport ($10.95 - Soft shell crab, spicy tuna, imitation crab, jalapeño, masago, cucumbers, red onions, tempura crunch, with chipotle mayo and eel sauce on soy paper) and a Mission ($8.95 - Salmon, ebi shrimp, cream cheese, pico de gallo, tortilla strips, romaine lettuce, with yuzu avocado cilantro on soy paper) to share. Both were made as combos, one with seaweed salad and one with taro chips that also comes with a side of queso cheese. It could be because we had just got off the plane but everything we had was quite tasty. I ended up swapping half my Mission for half a Rockport and by the time I finished my half of the Mission, I was too full to eat the Rockport. After a few bites of the Rockport, I gave it back and later regretted it because it was damn good. I like how both burritos had a crunchy element for texture. Yum! Those taro chips are also amazing and sweet. They didn't even need the queso.

Service here is great, the place was clean, and parking was plentiful. I want to go back like right now!
This place is always a win.  Fresh, delicious, great service, and too many options to count.  If I lived closer to this place, I'd be a regular there in a heartbeat.  I LOVE this place!!

My first sushi burrito experience and I would say it was a delicious burrito but I hated paying extra for avocado but they do give great portions of the raw fish I love. Go right when they open because it gets super busy after that. They were fast and the service was friendly. It's 4 stars because I have only gone once.

Sushi Burrito!? I mean how can you go wrong? I love sushi and when a friend mentioned this place, I was a little skeptical mainly because I'm a very picky eater and there's been complaints from other places. Today was the second time I've been there, and I was not disappointed! I got the Long Beach Burrito, and added cream cheese (extra$) and substituted guac for avocado.. it was perfect!!
As soon as you walk in, they greet you right away and are ready to help, especially if you've never been there before. The first time, they talked me through the process and they explained what my options were, including the fact that you can build your own! To my surprise, it was delicious. The prices are actually not bad at all, considering what you would normally pay for sushi and it's filling! A perfect balance. It can be too much (which is definitely NOT a bad thing) I ended up saving half for a little bit later. 
If a friend wouldn't of suggested this place I probably wouldn't of given it a try but I'm definitely glad I did! And you will be to! :)
Very fresh and tasty dishes. I had the Redondo Bowl with brown rice and it was very tasty, a good portion size and very good price for fresh fish.

Ok, How can I not give this place a shot? I have had this spot bookmarked for 2 months. I do like Burritos and I absolutely love Sushi. I went there with one mission. I wanted to get something with Salmon (my favorite thing in the world to eat) in a burrito. I walked myself in there and come to find out you have options on a bowl or a burrito. What? No I want seafood in a salad bowl. What is this???? I need a burrito!!!!! Then they asked me if I wanted flour or wheat. What??? Listen here lady, I want a sushi roll that looks exactly like a burrito. I don't want a salad or anything that even looks like it was ordered on a healthy menu. 

Once they were done, they handed something so beautiful and tasty I wanted to hit someone. 

My personal tip .........  Don't order a salad or anything outside of a sushi burrito.
Very refreshing food and you won't feel guilty after eating a sushi burrito! I have to find 9ne of these places back in California.
Excellent quality sushi burrito! Had the Redondo seaweed wrap.  Very fresh and heathy size serving.  My new favorite and highly recommended.
Place is fire. Good selection of fresh fish. The sauces are all different yet all delicious. There is a good amount of predetermined rolls and you can also make your own for an affordable price.

I got the Baja on nori..... Let me say woah! The flavor is incredibly fresh and well balanced. The place is clean and well kept.  It was lunch time so it was packed but the wait was well worth it.  I'll definitely be coming back!
I love the food but this is the second time i'm ordering and i didnt get the second sauce i ordered on my bowl... pretty annoyed but thats okay. Hopefully next time.
Omg Omg, I am so happy that we finally have our own sushi burrito!. This place rocks!, the food was delicious and the staffs are very friendly. I'll be a regular!
Amazing food! First time here and was definitely impressed! Whole family loved it!! Can't wait to come again!!!
